<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for a Custom (Meat and Poultry) Processor</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for a Custom (Meat and Poultry) Processor
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
Bureau of Meat & Poultry Inspection/Compliance Section<BR>
State Fairgrounds, P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
(217) 782-6684<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>		
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 650/1 - 20 (Meat & Poultry Inspection Act)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
This license is required to operate a custom processing facility where  animals and/or poultry are processed (cut up, packaged, wrapped, stored, frozen, smoked or cured) for use in the household.   A licensed custom operator may receive and process uninspected farm-butchered carcasses and process them for their owner.  Doing business without a license from the Department is a Class A misdemeanor and violators may be subject to fines up to $1,000 and/or a year in jail.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An application must be completed and filed with the Department.  If the business is operating under an assumed name, the application must include proof of registration with the County Clerk's office. If the business is a corporation, the application must demonstrate that it is registered with the Secretary of State.  Applicant must submit to the Department blueprints of the facility. (For new facilities, blueprints must be approved before construction begins.)  The Department's Regional Administrator must inspect and approve the facility before a license will be issued.  The average time for processing a license is 4 to 5 weeks.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicant must have no prior convictions of violating the Meat & Poultry Inspection Act.  The facility must conform to the requirements of the USDA 570 Handbook.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The fee for the license is $50.00.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
