<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Participation in Arbitration of Seed Disputes</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Participation in Arbitration of Seed Disputes
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9281<BR>
Bureau of Agricultural Products Inspection<BR>
(217) 785-1082<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
5050 Illinois Compiled Statutes 110/1 et seq. (Seed Arbitration Act)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Before a seed purchaser (most usually a farmer) may sue a seed company for failure of any seed (except flower seeds) to produce or perform as represented by the package label, a farmer must first submit the claim to arbitration the Arbitration Review Committee.  The seller/seed company must participate in the arbitration proceedings.  Failure of a party to participate in arbitration does not constitute a defense in court for the other party.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The purchaser begins the arbitration procedure by filing a verified complaint with the Department.  Upon receipt of a complaint the Department will serve a copy of the complaint to the seller by certified mail.  A Department Review Committee will make a recommendation to the purchaser (farmer) based on an evaluation of the validity of the claim.  If the purchaser chooses to pursue the arbitration process, the Review Committee will refer the complaint to the Seed Arbitration Council (which may recommend doing more testing).
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The fee to file a complaint is $200.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
