<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Recording of Livestock Brands.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Recording of Livestock Brands.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
Bureau of Animal Welfare<BR>
P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9281<BR>
(217) 782-6657<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
510 Illinois Compiled Statutes 40 / 1 Thru 17  (Illinois Brand Act)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A business that wants to identify livestock with a hot-iron brand must register the brand with the Department.  Registration authorizes the business to use a brand not already being used, and to adopt that brand for its exclusive use. Use of a unrecorded brand is a violation of the Brand Act and is a Class C misdemeanor.  Registration remains valid for 5 years.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Interested parties must complete and file with the Department forms #LB-1 and #LB-2, including a scale diagram of the proposed brand and the location on the animal to be branded.  The Department will deny an application if the proposed brand is already registered, or if it so closely resembles another registered brand that it cannot be readily distinguished.  If  an application is accepted, the Department will issue a Brand Certificate and file the brand in the Brand Book.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A brand is considered personal property of a business and notice of the sale, assignment or transfer of a registered brand must be given to the Department.  Brands may be applied only to an animal's shoulder, ribs, or hip on either the right or left side.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The fee to record a brand is $15 for a 5 year period.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
