<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration for selling, installing or repairing a commercially-used weighing device</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>


<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration for selling, installing or repairing a commercially-used weighing device
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
Bureau of Weights & Measures<BR>
State Fairgrounds, P.O.Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9281<BR>
(217) 785-8252<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
470 Illinois Compiled Statutes, Section 8.1  Weights & Measures Act
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 8 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter I, Subpart E, Section 600.450-560.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Any person or company selling, installing, servicing or repairing a commercially-used weighing or measuring device is required to be Registered by the Department.  <P>

Operating without a Registration is a business offense subject to a minimum fine of $500 for the first offense; $1,500 for a second, and $2,500 for a third offense.  <P>

Registration is valid for one year.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for Registration must file an "Application for Registered Service Company & Registered Serviceperson Certificate" Form# IL 406-0187.    <P>

Applicants also must have available standards and testing equipment appropriate in design and adequate in amount to provide the services for the proposed Registration, pass a qualifying examination for each type of weighing or measuring device applicant intends to install or service, demonstrate a working knowledge of weighing or measuring devices that the applicant intends to install or service, have a working knowledge of all appropriate weights and measures laws and rules, and have available a current copy of NIST Handbook.<P>

The processing time depends upon how quickly the applicant passes the qualifying examination and demonstrates a working knowledge of the weighing or measuring devices they intend to install or service.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registrants must file a "Placed-Into-Service Report" within 5 days of placing a weighing or measuring device into service.  <P>

A decal must be placed upon a commercially-used weighing or measuring device indicating that the device has been placed into service by a registered serviceperson.  <P>

All standards and testing equipment must be calibrated once every two years in a NIST approved Metrology Laboratory.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>
$5 per Serviceperson<P>
$25 per Company
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
