<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Reporting of Dairy Statistics</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Reporting of Dairy Statistics
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
Bureau of Agricultural Statistics<BR>
P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9281<BR>
(217) 492-4295<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
505 Illinois Compiled Statutes 50/0-3. (Dairy Statistics Act)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Owners/operators of dairy plants (including plants producing cheese, ice cream and any other dairy products) are required to provide annual reports of statistical data, including production and marketing information, to the Illinois Agricultural Statistics Service.  The Department mails survey forms to dairy plant owner/operators, who must complete and return the forms to the Illinois Agricultural Statistics Service within 30 days.<P> 

Failure to comply is a petty offense and may result of fines up to $100.
</DD></DL>

