<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Soil Amendments Registration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Soil Amendments Registration
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Agriculture<BR>
P.O. Box 19281<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9281<BR>
Bureau of Agricultural Products Inspection<BR>
(217) 785-8356<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
505 Illinois Compiled Statutes120/1 et seq. (Soil Amendment Act)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A business that manufactures or distributes soil amendments. must register each separately identified soil amendment with the Department before distribution may begin.  Violations are a business offense punishable by fines at least $1,000, plus  costs.  Registration is valid for one year.  All registrations expire on December 31. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
To register, applicants must complete and file an "Application for Registration of Soil Amendments" and a "Substantiation Format for Soil Amendments" instruction sheet.  A copy of the label of the amendment to be registered must be submitted with the application along with any advertising literature.  (The label must include the net weight, brand or product name, guaranteed analysis, purpose of the product, directions for use and the name and address of registrant).<P> 

Applicants must substantiate claims made for the product and proof of value and usefulness for the soil amendment.  Approval usually takes about 6 weeks.  The Department may refuse to register a soil amendment if the composition of the soil amendment does not warrant the claims made.  If  registration is denied, the process is subject to the Administrative Review Law.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Labels must appear on the face or display side in a readable and conspicuous form on every soil amendment product container or must accompany each bulk order.  The product must meet label guarantees.  Registrant must allow access to product and records during  regular business hours for inspectors.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The fee to register each product is $250.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
