<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Application for the use of the word	"Bank," "Banker" or "Banking," or their derivatives, in connection with a business not engaged in banking.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>


<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application for the use of the word	"Bank," "Banker" or "Banking," or their derivatives, in connection with a business not engaged in banking.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Commissioner of Banks and Trust Companies<BR> 	
Corporate Applications Divisions<BR>
310 South Michigan Avenue, Suite 2130<BR>
Chicago, IL 60604<BR>
(312) 793-2043<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
205 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5 / 46<P>
805 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5 / 4.05 (a)(2)(ii)
</DD></DL>

<HR> 
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Before a person, firm, partnership or corporation may use the terms "bank," "banker" or "banking" in a business, permission must be received from the Commissioner.<P>
 
The Commissioner of Banks and Trusts (CBT) must grant authorization for use of the words "bank," "banker" or "banking" in a business.  Businesses that use these terms without authorization are contacted by the Commissioner and required to make an application. <P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Businesses desiring to use these words in an business name must complete and file an "Application for the use of the word 'Bank', 'Banker' or 'Banking'", describing the business name, address, phone number, any proposed name, address and phone number, if applicable; a full description of the nature of the business, including any customer/client contacts where customary financial institution services have been rendered, and a description of the manner in which the applicant intends to use these word; and, the name, address and phone number of a contact person who can offer additional information about the applicant.<P> 

To assure that a business does not misleadingly represent itself to the public, the CBT may require applicants to meet certain conditions before authority is given.  Business that do not have banking powers generally may not use these words without authority.  Processing an application usually takes two weeks.  The most frequent reason for denial of an application is because these terms would mislead the public. There is no appeal process.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Businesses allowed by the Commissioner to use these words in their business names must not represent itself, through advertising or other means, as a bank or type of financial institution, and must not engage in banking, and must comply with all conditions deemed appropriate by the CBT. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
