<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Application for the use of the word "Trust," "Trustee," or "Fiduciary," or their derivatives, by a business not engaged in banking or as a corporate fiduciary.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application for the use of the word "Trust," "Trustee," or "Fiduciary," or their derivatives, by a business not engaged in banking or as a corporate fiduciary.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Commissioner of Banks and Trust Companies<BR>
Corporate Applications Division<BR>
310 South Michigan Avenue, Suite 2130<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60604<BR>
(312) 793-2043<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
205 Illinois Compiled Statutes 620 / 1-9 (Corporate Fiduciary Act)<P>
805 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5 / 4.05 (a) (2) (iii) (Business Corporation Act)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
No business may use the words "trust," "trustee" or "fiduciary" in its name without approval from the Commissioner.  Businesses attempting to use these words in a business name are contacted by the Commissioner and required to make an application.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>

<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete and file with the Commissioner an "Application to use the word 'Trust,' 'Trustee' or 'Fiduciary'", if any of those words or their derivatives are proposed to be used by a business not engaging in banking or a corporate fiduciary.<P>

The application must contain applicant's business name, address, phone number, proposed name, address and phone number; a detailed description of the nature of the business including any customer/client contacts involving customary financial institution services, the manner in which the word will be used, and the name, address and phone number of a contact person who can provide additional information.<P>

The Commissioner reviews applications to make sure the business will not act as a fiduciary and that the use of "trust," "trustee" or "fiduciary" will not be misleading to the public.  Applications are usually processed in about two weeks.  Applications are most often denied because of use of these words would be misleading. There is no appeal process.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicant must comply with all conditions deemed appropriate by the Commissioner.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

