<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Contracting with not for profit community-based service agencies to provide a comprehensive and integrated system of Youth Services.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Contracting with not for profit community-based service agencies to provide a comprehensive and integrated system of Youth Services.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Children and Family Services<BR>
Bureau of Operations and Community Services<BR>
406 E. Monroe<BR>
Springfield, Illinois  62701<BR>
(217) 785-2570<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
23 Illinois Compiled Statutes 505, Section 5.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 89, Illinois Administrative Code, Part 310.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The Department provides funding for the Comprehensive Community-Based Youth Services (CCBYS) program to help reduce the number of youths in the Child Welfare and Juvenile Justice systems.<P>

The CCBYS provider performs or arranges for these services:  24 hours crisis intervention response system (responds to referrals from police/court and the Department's Child Welfare and Child Protection divisions, for emergency/crisis situations such as runaway and family conflicts and reconcilliations that can't be handled by police); Family counseling, individual counseling, and the establishment of a support system for members of the family of a youth experiencing severe crisis/separation from the family; Organizing community volunteers to provide services or remediate conditions affecting youth; Individual and/or group counseling. Employment and educational assistance; Drug/alcohol education; Liaison to DCFS field or site offices, court and police personnel.<P>  
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
CCBYS provider applicants must apply to the Department for a License  as Child Welfare Agency.  Once an applicant is Licensed as a provider by the Department, they can begin to accept referrals and provide services to youth and families.<P>

Contracts are awarded to CCBYS providers on the basis of competitive applications.  CCBYS providers are reimbursed for their services based on the dollar amount of their contract.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
