<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Household Goods Operating Authority (HHG),
Public Carrier Certificate  (PCC),
Relocator License, Operator Permit, Dispatcher Permit</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Household Goods Operating Authority  (HHG)<BR>
Public Carrier Certificate  (PCC)<BR>
Relocator License, Operator Permit, Dispatcher Permit<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Commerce Commission<BR>
527 East Capitol, P.O.Box 19280<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9280<BR>
Transportation Division<BR>
(217) 782-4654<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
625 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/18c-1101 Illinois Commercial Transportation  Law <P>

625 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/18a-100. Relocation of Trespassing Vehicle Law<P>
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
92 Illinois Adminstrative Code 1201 - 2100
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required from the Commerce Commission  to operate as a For-Hire motor carrier (PCC),  a Household Goods (HHG) carrier, or as a Relocation Tower. Conducting these businesses without a license is a violation of the law and may result in civil penalties including loss of driving privileges.  HHG and PCC licenses are awarded once and may be renewed annually by the purchase from the Commission of per-vehicle "cab cards". Cab cards must be carried in all trucks operated by licensed carriers.<P>

Relocation Tower licenses expire every two years and must be renewed by Commission order.  <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A public hearing is held only for household goods operating authorities.<P>

Public Carrier Certificate (PCC) applicants must complete and file with the Commission a form with applicable fee, and proof of insurance. <P>

Household Goods Operating Authority applicants must complete and file with the Commission a form with applicable fees, proof that applicant is " fit, willing and able to provide service", and have supporting shippers testify at a hearing that the proposed service is needed.<P>

Notice of the application must be published in the official State Newspaper.<P>

Relocator Authority applicants must complete and file with the Commission  a form with the applicable fee. Notice of the application must be published in the official State Newspaper.  <P>

A background check of applicant and all operators/dispatchers is required. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
All carriers must file proof of insurance. Household Goods carriers must  publish rates.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG><EM>PCC:</EM></STRONG> Certificate is $300; Per-vehicle fee is $6; Single State Registration Fees: Interstate operators is $7, plus other state's fees.  Proof-of-Insurance filing  is $25.<P>
<STRONG><EM>Household Goods Authority</EM></STRONG> is $600;  per-vehicle fee is $25; Proof-of-Insurance is $25.<P>
<STRONG><EM>Relocation Tower License</EM></STRONG> is $600 (renewal is $600)<P>
<STRONG><EM>Operator's permit</EM></STRONG> is $60 (renewal is $40)<P>
<STRONG><EM>Dispatcher's permit</EM></STRONG> is $60.00 (renewal permit is $40.00) .<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
