<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Pre-Need Cemetery Sales Act</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Pre-Need Cemetery Sales Act
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Office of the Comptroller<BR>
Cemetery and Burial Trust Department<BR>
100 West Randolph Street, Suite 15-500<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60601<BR>
(312) 814-5783<BR>
</dd></dl><hr>

<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<dl><dd>
815 Illinois Compiled Statutes 390/1 et seq. (Illinois Pre-Need Cemetery Sales Act)
</dd></dl>
<H3>Regulation:
</H3><dl><dd>
74 Illinois Administrative Code, Part(s) 310
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<dl><dd>
The purpose of the Act is to assure adequate protection for those who contract through pre-need contracts (agreements for furnishing funeral services) for the purchase of certain cemetery merchandise and cemetery services and undeveloped interment, entombment or inurnment space, when the seller may delay delivery or performance more than 120 days following initial payment on the account. All persons that offer for sale or sell cemetery merchandise, cemetery services or undeveloped interment, entombment or inurnment spaces on a pre-need basis are required to be licensed by the Office of the Comptroller. This Act does not apply to religious, municipal, state or federal cemeteries. Any person
violating this Act is guilty of a Class 4 felony, and may be subject to fines and a civil action. Licenses must be posted in the place of business. Each business location must be licensed. Individual salesperson are not required to be licensed. Licenses are in effect indefinitely or until it is canceled by the licensee or revoked by the Comptroller.<p></dd></dl><hr>

<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Applicants must submit an Illinois Pre-Need Cemetery Sales - Application for License, in writing to the State Comptroller. Applications must include the name; home and business address of the applicant, every member, member of the Board of Directors, officer, director and shareholder (holding 5% or more of the corporate stock). A detailed statement of the applicant's assets and liabilities, a detailed statement of every member, board director, officer, director, and shareholder, the name of the trustee, and any advisors, copy of the proposed trust agreement, names of the corporate surety company providing the performance bond for construction and a copy of the bond, where applicable, must also be submitted. Complete applications are generally processed within one week. Before refusing to issue, suspension or revocation of the license, the Comptroller holds a hearing to determine if the applicant is entitled to hold a license. The Comptroller may refuse to issue, suspend or revoke a license if there are any misrepresentations, if the applicant/licensee is insolvent; for fraudulent practices; omission of pertinent data; for failure to make an annual report, or failure to comply with the Act. Final Administrative decisions of the Comptroller fall under judicial review. <p></dd></dl><hr>

<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites, Post-Requisites:  
</H3><dl>
<dt><strong>Co-Requisite: </strong><dd>Applicants must submit a fidelity bond to the Comptroller in the amount of 10% of the trust fund on hand, not to exceed $10,000 at the time of application. After the first year's report is filed, the requirement is then 10% of all trust funds held, not to exceed $100,000. Licensees must keep accurate accounts, books and records for all transactions, copies of agreements, dates and amounts of payments made or received, the names and addresses of the contracting parties, and of those
persons for whose benefit the funds are received, and the names of the trust depositories. Licensees must submit annual reports to the Comptroller within 75 days after the end of the licensees fiscal year.<P>
<dt><strong> Post-Requisite: </strong><dd>Records must be maintained for 3 years after fulfilling the obligations of the contract. <p></dl><hr>

<H3>VII. Fee:
</H3>
<dl><dd>$25 application fee 
</dd></dl>






<HR>
