<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration of Crematories</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:
</H3><dl><dd>
Registration of Crematories
</dd></dl><hr>

<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Office of the Comptroller<BR>
Cemetery and Burial Trust Department<BR>
100 West Randolph Street, Suite 15-500<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60601<BR>
(312) 814-5783<BR>
</dd></dl><hr>

<H3>III. Statute:
</H3><dl><dd>
410 Illinois Compiled Statutes 18/1 et seq. (Crematory Regulation Act)
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Any person doing business in this State or any cemetery, funeral establishment, corporation, partnership, joint venture, voluntary organization or any other entity, may erect maintain and operate a crematory in Illinois and provide the necessary appliances and facilities for the cremation of human remains.  All crematories must register with the Office of the Comptroller. Crematories are subject to all local, state, and federal health and environmental protection requirements and must obtain all necessary licenses and permits from the Illinois Department of Public Health, the federal Department of Health and Human Services and the Illinois and federal Environmental Protection Agency. Crematories must re-register with the Comptroller each year, on or before March 15 or within 75 days after the end of their fiscal year.
<p>
Violations of this Act may result in penalties ranging from a Class B misdemeanor to a Class 4 Felony. Violations may also be brought before the Attorney General for prosecution. 
<p></dd></dl><hr>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Applicants must submit a Crematory Registration Application for registration as a Crematory Authority to the Comptroller. Registration allows an Authority to operate a crematory. The application must include the full name, business and home address for the applicant and any member of the partnership, board of directors, officer, director or
shareholder (holding more than 25% of the stock), the address and location of the crematory, and a description of the type of structure and equipment to be used in operation of the crematory. Applications are generally processed within two weeks.  Applications may be denied for incomplete information. 
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites, Post-Requisites: 
</H3>
<dl>
<dt><STRONG>Co-Requisite</STRONG> <dd>Each crematory authority must file with the Comptroller, an annual report, including information on any changes that have occurred. Reports must be filed on or before March 15 every year or within 75 days after the end of its fiscal year.  A penalty of $5 per day may be assessed for delinquency in filing the report. The Crematory Authority must maintain a permanent  record of each cremation that took place at its facility, containing the name of the decedent, date of the cremation, and the final disposition of the cremated remains. 
</dl><hr>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<dl><dd>
The application fee is $50. Annual reports must be submitted with $25. 
</dd></dl>






