<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Certification for Illinois property tax relief and federal rapid amortization for pollution control facilities.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>


<H3>I. Business requirements Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Certification for Illinois property tax relief and federal rapid amortization for pollution control facilities.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Environmental Protection Agency<BR>
Division of Water Pollution Control/Bureau of Water<BR>
2200 Churchill Road<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9276<BR>
(217)782-0610<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
35 Illinois Compiled Statutes 205, Section 111
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 86 Illinois Administrative Code, Part 1910.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The purpose of this certification process is to verify that water pollution control equipment meets the definition requirements of "pollution control facilities". This certification can result in a State tax reduction or Federal income tax incentive, but requires certification from the IEPA before tax relief will be granted.  Water Pollution Control Equipment only needs to be certified once to obtain tax relief & or federal amortization.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for certification must file with the Agency a completed  application form available from the Division of Water Pollution Control.  If applicant satisfies the requirements for "pollution control facilities" the Agency will certify that tax relief and federal rapid amortization for pollution control facilities is appropriate.  The certification process usually takes 2-3 months.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-requisites & Post-requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
