<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Safety Deposit License Act</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Safety Deposit License Act
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>II. Agency:
</H3><dl><dd>
Department of Financial Institutions<BR>
Consumer Credit Division<BR>
100 West Randolph, Suite 15-700<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60601<BR>
(312) 814-5145  <BR>
</dd></dl><hr>

<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<dl><dd>
240 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/0.01 et seq. (Safety Deposit License Act) 
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:
</H3><dl><dd>
Entities renting or permitting compensation for the use of safety deposit boxes, safes, vaults or other facilities for safekeeping personal property must be licensed. The license does not apply to banks, savings and loan institutions or credit union, etc. All business locations must be licensed. Licenses expire every July 1. Renewal applications must be submitted by July 1. Violation of this Act is a petty offense. Every day of non-compliance is considered a separate offense.
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>V. Approval Process:
</H3><dl><dd>
Applicants must complete and submit to the Department of Financial Institutions - Consumer Credit Division, a license application for Safety Deposit Boxes, Safes and Vaults, a supplemental statement of the applicant's history and business experiences, a vault inspection certificate, fingerprints of all the principals specifically the owners, officers, directors and stockholders, and specimen contracts aka example of contracts. Applications are usually reviewed within 45 days. Applications may be denied if the applicant is not a US citizen, has been convicted of a felony, has not provided a burglar alarm system for the safe, vault, and other fixtures. All denied applications are subject to an Administrative Review Process.
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites: </H3>
<dl>
<dt><strong>Post-Requisite:  </strong><dd>Each license location is examined annually by the Department.
</dl><hr>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<dl><dd>

Initial and Renewal License Fees:     $50.
</dd></dl>





<HR>
