<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Sales Finance Agency Act License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Sales Finance Agency Act License
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Department of Financial Institutions<BR>
Consumer Credit Division<BR>
100 West Randolph, Suite 15-700<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60601<BR>
(312) 814-5145  <BR>
</dd></dl><hr>

<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<dl><dd>
205 Illinois Compiled Statutes 660/1 (Sales Finance Agency Act)  
</dd></dl>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<dl><dd>
38 Illinois Administrative Code Chapter I, Part 160 (Sales Finance Agency Act)
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Entities engaged in the business of purchasing or making loans secured by retail installment sales contracts, retail charge agreements or their outstanding balances must be licensed. All business locations must be licensed. Conducting business without a license is a Class A misdemeanor. Licenses expire every December 31. Renewal applications must be renewed no later than December 1 of each year.
 <p></dd></dl><hr>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Applicants must complete and submit to the Department of Financial Institutions - Consumer Credit Division, a license application for the Sales Finance Agency Act, a supplemental application(s), a credit report(s), and financial statements.  Applications are frequently denied due to failure to comply with Sections 8.1 through 8.12 or Section 9 of the Act. Applications are usually reviewed within 45 days. Denied applications may be reviewed through a hearing.
<p></dd></dl><hr>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites: 
</H3><dl>
<dt><STRONG>Post-Requisite:  </STRONG><dd>Each licensed location is examined annually by the Department.
</dl><hr>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<dl><dd>
License Fee: $300 (Annual) or $150 (Semi-Annual). The annual fee is for applications received for a full year. The Semi-Annual fee is for applications received for January 1 through June 30 and July 1 through December 31. All applications are due in one installment.<P>

Branch Office(s): $100 (Annual) or $50 (Semi-Annual). The Annual fee is for applications received for a full year. The Semi-Annual fee is for applications received from January 1 through June 30 and July 1 through December 31. All applications are due in one installment. <P>

Relocation: $25 within same County; New License Application if relocating outside the County. <P>

Name Change: $25<P>

Renewal License: $300 for Main Office + $100 for each Branch Office.<P>

Annual Exam: $100 / Per Examiner, Per Day. An examination is usually conducted by one examiner.<P>
</dl>






<HR>
