<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Title Insurance Act</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Title Insurance Act
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Department of Financial Institutions<BR>
Consumer Credit Division / Title Insurance Section<BR>
500 Iles Park Place, Suite 314<BR>
Springfield, Illinois  62718<BR>
(217) 785-6990<BR>
</dd></dl><hr>

<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<dl><dd>
215 Illinois Compiled Statutes 155 (Title Insurance Act)
</dd></dl>
<H3>Regulation:
</H3><dl><dd>
50 Illinois Administrative Code Chapter V, Part 8100
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Title Insurance Companies that guarantee or insure title to real estate must have a certificate from the Department which states that the company has deposited, for the benefit of its creditors, government bonds or securities in amounts that may vary with the population of the county in which the real estate is located for which policies are issued.  <P>

Title Insurance Agents must be registered with the Department by a title insurance company (and be authorized by that company) to determine insurability of title in accordance with underwriting rules and standards. <P>

Independent Escrowees who receive (escrow) deposits in trust of funds or documents for the purpose of effecting the sale, transfer, encumbrance or lease of real estate subject to a prescribed condition, must have a Certificate of Authority from the Department and place government bonds or securities on deposit for the benefit of its creditors.<P>
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Title Insurance Company's  must submit an application containing such things as audited financial statements, a history of the company, information from the state of domicile (if not an Illinois company), copies of previous examinations of the business, and listings of securities to be place on deposit. Applications are usually processed in 90 to 120 days.  <P>

Title Insurance Agents must submit an Application for Registration for each title insurance company for which they will act as a title insurance agent.  Applications must be submitted to the Department by the title insurance companies. Agent registrations are usually processed in 2 or 3 days. <P>

Independent Escrowees must submit an application with information including audited financial statements, history of the company, listing of securities to be placed on deposit, and a list of all Illinois counties in which the company intends to conduct business.  Applications are usually processed in 90 to 120 days.<P></dd></dl><hr>

<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites:  </H3>
<dl>
<dt><STRONG>Co-Requisites: </STRONG><dd>Title Insurance Companies with a Certificate of Authority issued by the Department must file an Annual Registration of all Insurance Agents on forms prescribed by the Director, an Annual Statement of Condition which includes an annual report, audited financial statements, statement of financial condition (as well as other financial information if a corporation domiciled outside the State of Illinois), and file an Annual Computation of Retaliatory Fees. Independent Escrowees must file an Annual Statement of Condition with the Department which includes detailed financial information for the previous year.<P></dl><hr>

<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Title Insurance Company: Original application for Certificate of Authority: $500; Certificate of Authority: $10; Annual Statement of Condition: $50; Annual  Examination: $300 per examiner per day, plus all travel related expenses.  <P>

Title Insurance Agents: Annual Registration: $1 for each policy issued in the preceding calendar year, but not to exceed $20,000 per year. Annual Examination fee: $300 per examiner per day plus all travel related expenses. <P>

Independent Escrowee: Original application for Certificate of Authority under the Title Insurance Act: $500; Certificate of Authority: $10; Annual statement: $50; Examination, if required: $300 per examiner, per day plus all travel related expenses. <P>

Registered title insurance agent:  Audit or examination, if required: $300 per examiner, per day plus all travel related expenses.<P>
</dd></dl>






