<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Transmitters of Money Act License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:
</H3><dl><dd>
Transmitters of Money Act License
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>II. Agency:
</H3><dl><dd>
Department of Financial Institutions<BR>
Consumer Credit Division<BR>
100 West Randolph, Suite 15-700<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60601<BR>
(312) 814-5145 <BR>
</dd></dl><hr> 

<H3>III. Statute:
</H3><dl><dd>
205 Illinois Compiled Statutes 675/1 (Transmitters of Money Act)
</dd></dl>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<dl><dd>
Transmitters of Money Act P.A. 88-643 
</dd></dl><hr>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<dl><dd>
A license is required to sell or issue payment instruments, transit money or exchange, for compensation payment instruments or money of the US government or a foreign government, to or from money of another government.  
<p>
Licenses are valid for one year and expire on December 31. Renewal applications must be received by December 1 of each year. Conducting business without a license is a Class A misdemeanor. 
<p></dd></dl><hr>
<H3>V. Approval Process:
</H3><dl><dd>
Applicants must complete and submit a license application for the Transmitter of Money Act, together with personal background information for all principals including employment history and previous litigation, a $100,000 to $1,000,000 bond, certified financial statements and a list of proposed business locations. Applications are usually reviewed within 60 days. Applications may be denied for insolvency, failure to permit an examination, material misstatement on the application or violation of a material statutory provision. Denied applications may be appealed through a hearing. </dd></dl><hr>

<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites:  </H3>
<dl>
<dt><strong>Co-Requisites:  </strong><dd>Licensees must submit a quarterly report of "authorized sellers" who were added or deleted from the previous quarter, together with a $10 fee for each additional authorized seller.   Renewal applications must include an audited Financial Statement.
</dl><hr>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<dl><dd>
License Fee: $100 plus $10 for each additional location<BR>
Application Fee: $100<BR>
Renewal License: $100 plus $10 for each additional location<BR>
Authorized Seller: $10 each<BR>
Service of Process authorizing the Director to accept legal notices against the licenses: $ 10 <BR>

</dd></dl>





<HR>
