<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Suppliers Licenses</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Suppliers Licenses
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Gaming Board / Department of Revenue<BR>
Enforcement Division<BR>
160 North LaSalle St., 3rd floor<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 814-4700<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
230 Illinois Compiled Statutes 10/1
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 80 Illinois Administrative Code, Part 3000.100
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Suppliers License is required to sell or lease, and to contract to sell
or lease, gambling equipment and supplies to any licensed party involved in
the ownership or management of gambling operations.  Persons are not
eligible to receive a Suppliers License include anyone convicted of a
felony,  persons submitting false information on an application, members of
the Board, persons licensed in another jurisdiction whose license has been
revoked. Applicants must provide the Board with a list of equipment,
devices and supplies offered for sale or lease in connection with authorized gambling games.  Licenses are valid for one year and may be renewed to qualified candidates.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file a "Supplier's Application Form" after which the Board
will begin background investigations.  The time required to process
applications varies according to the time required for the background
investigation.  Reasons for denial could include any conduct by the
licensee considered in violation of the Act and rules established by the
Board.  Applicants who are denied a License may request a hearing.  The
Board may suspend, revoke or restrict the License of anyone violating Board
rules or regulations, for "cause" which would have disqualified applicant
had that information been known to the Board at the time of licensure, or
for default in payment of debts or obligations to the State.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License holders must file a quarterly return with the Board listing all
sales and leases.  License holders must file an annual report listing its
inventories of gambling equipment, devices and supplies.  License holders
must permanently affix its name to its equipment, devices and supplies for
gambling operations.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<PRE>
Application Fee:         $10,000
Annual License Fee:      $ 5,000 
</PRE>
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
