<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Workers' Compensation Insurance, and Self Insurance.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>


<H3>I. Business Requirement Profile:</H3>

<DL><DD> Workers' Compensation Insurance, and Self Insurance.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. Agency:</H3>

<DL><DD>Illinois Industrial Commission<BR>
Office of Self-insurance Administration<BR>
701 South Second Street<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 6270<BR>
(217) 785-7084<BR>
 *NCCI Phone #:  (217) 793-1100.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>

<DL><DD>820 Illinois Compiled Statutes 305/4.</DD></DL>
<DL><DD><H3>Regulation: </H3></DD></DL>

<DL><DD>50 Illinois Administrative Code 7100</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>

<DL><DD><P>Any employer engaged in a business declared
to be "extra hazardous" by the provisions of Section 3 of the Workers'
Compensation Act, or who elects to provide any pay compensation provided
for in the Act, must insure payment of compensation by obtaining approval
from the Industrial Commission to self-insure, or by insuring its entire
liability through an insurance carrier authorized, licensed or permitted to
do business in Illinois.

<P>Failure to comply with the insurance requirement may result in a fine of up
to $500 per day.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>

<DL><DD><P>Employers must either:

<P>1.) Provide proof of insurance by filing a certificate of insurance with:

 <DL> <DD><P>  *National Council on Compensation Insurance<BR>
     P.O. Box 19403<BR>
     Springfield, Illinois 62705, or<BR></DD></DL>

<P>2.) Apply for approval to self-insure  by filing an application with:

   <DL><DD><P> Illinois Industrial Commission, Office of Self-insurance  Administration<BR>
     701 South Second Street<BR>
     Springfield, Illinois 62704.<BR></DD></DL>

<P>Applications to self insure are reviewed by the Self-Insurers Advisory
Board, which makes a recommendation to the Chairman of the Industrial
Commission, who then issues a decision.

<P>Criteria for reviewing applications and financial statements is described
in the Illinois Administrative Code.  Applications may be denied if
applicant's financial statement does not warrant approval of self-insurance
or if  the employer fails to furnish required security.

<P>Denied applications may be appealed to the Circuit Court.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites: </H3>

<DL><DD>Applications for
self-insurance must be accompanied by applicant's current financial
statement.  Renewal applications must be filed annually and submitted at
least 60 days prior to the requested effective date of self-insurance.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>

<DL><DD>Employers applying for approval to self-insure must pay a non-
refundable fee of $500.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
