<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Certification of Farm Labor Contractors who recruit or transport farm workers in the state of Illinois </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Certification of Farm Labor Contractors who recruit or transport farm workers in the state of Illinois 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Labor<BR>
Fair Labor Standards Division <BR>
160 N. LaSalle<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 793-2804<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 505/1 et seq.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
This statute requires contractors who recruit or transport farm workers within the State, and their full time employees, to register with the Department and carry and display a certifiction card at all times. Contractors must post at each work location the Terms and Conditions of employment in a language familiar to the farmworker.  The Terms and Conditions must contain information prescribed by the Department (including rates of pay, method of payment, the type of crop, and whether transportation is provided) and be prominently displayed. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applications must be submitted to the agency prior to the contracting and approval must be received.  All cards must be completed.  <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Contractors must  maintain records of employment, including names of employees,  proof of hours worked, pay rates and wage payments.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
$50.00 annually
</DD></DL>


<HR>
