<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Illinois Street Trades Law</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Street Trades Law
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Labor<BR>
Fair Labor Standards Division<BR>
160 N. LaSalle<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 793-2804<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
820 Illinois Compiled Statutes 215
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An employer  must have a certificate from the Department before employing a minor in any street trade*   Certification is required of any employer who employs minors 14 and 15 years of age to solicit, sell or distribute products or services. Each certificate issued by the Department is accompanied by 10 permit forms. Employers must issue to each minor employed in a street trade, a permit on the Department form.  Permits are not transferrable and must be carrried at all times by the minor while engaged in the street trade minor employed.  Such forms must be carried by the minor at all times while engaged in the Employers must inform the agency within 2 days when a permit is issued, giving the minor's name, address and other information.  <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Employer must file with the Department a completed application and fee. Violations of the Act is a Class C misdemeanor and violators will be fined $500.  <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Pre-Requisites </EM>- Minors must have a valid Employment Certificate issued by the Superintendent of  Schools.<P>

<EM>Co-Requisites</EM> -  Display upon request by any police officer, truant officer or agent of  the Department  of the required certificates.<P>

Submit to the Department additional information of minors recently hired who were issued permits from the employer.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
$50.00.<P>

*Street trade is the sale, offering for sale, soliciting, collecting, displaying or distributing any item of personal property or service, including shoe shining, or distribution of advertising materials (except the sale or distribution of or taking orders for periodicals delivered by the minor, or activity on behalf of  a not-for-profit organization the minor or his/her family belongs to).<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
