<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Private Employment Agencies Act </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Private Employment Agencies Act 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Labor <BR>
Fair Labor Standards Division/Private Employment Agency Section<BR>
160 N. LaSalle<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 793-1817<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 515/1 et seq.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code, sections 680.00 et seq.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An Agency license is required to engage "for gain or profit"in the business of securing or attempting to secure employment for persons seeking employment, or attempting to secure employees for employers.  <P>

A Counselor's license is required for any employee of an employment agency who interviews, counsels or advises applicants or employers, or both, on employment or related matters, or makes or arranges contracts of employment between employers and employees.  Having a license allows a business to charge a fee to either the employer or employee.  Conducting business without a license is a Class B misdemeanor.  Both agency and counselor licenses are valid for one year. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An application-for-license form, available from the Department, must be completed and filed together with applicable fees. Applications are processed in 60 days. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
 Businesses applying for a license must submit certain information, including  background information of each officer, owner or person with a financial interest in the business, their net worth statements, a list of estimated, projected operating expenses for the first three months of business,  a bond,  a orporation's certificate of incorporation or partnership's signed partnership agreement and character affidavits. Applicants must submit for the Department's approval, certain forms and documents such as referral slip, job order, fee schedule and refund policy, fee transaction record, and any contracts.  Counselors must pass an examination on applicable 	laws within 90 days of  application. Applications for new counselors must include: agency affiliation,  recent work experience, affidavits of moral character, and other information. Agency address and counselor residence changes must be reported in writing to the Department. Licenses of counselors no longer employed by an agency must be returned to Department. Transfer of counselor licenses between agencies must be requested in writing.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Agency license fees range between $250 and $500, depending upon the number counselors in an Agency. The initial fee for a Counselor is $50.00, and the annual renewal fee is $25.00.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
