<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: The Illinois Minimum Wage Law  </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The Illinois Minimum Wage Law  
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Labor<BR>
Fair Labor Standards Division<BR>
160 N. LaSalle<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 793-2804<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
820 Illinois Compiled Statutes 105
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Businesses employing four or more workers must pay a specific minimum wage, time-an-one-half to employees who work over 40 hours per week, and must satisfy certain recordkeeping requirements. Limited exemptions to both the minimum wage and overtime provisions exist. A Subminimum Wage license may be issued upon application and authorization by the Department.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Businesses applying for  a license to pay employees a wage less than the minimum wage must file an application together with  support information and documentation justifying the wage. A license to pay less than minimum wage must be secured prior to payment of wages.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Employers must keep records for three years of information including (but not limited to):  each employee's name, address, occupation, rate of pay, the amount paid each pay period, hours worked each day and week, and other information as may be required by the Department.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
