<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Blaster's Certification for Blasting Operations in Surface Coal Mining</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Blaster's Certification for Blasting Operations in Surface Coal Mining
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Office of Mines & Minerals  (OMM)<BR>
Land Reclamation Division<BR>
524 South Second Street<BR>
Springfield, IL 62701-1787<BR>
(217) 782-4970<BR>
TDD:  (217) 524-4626<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 720 (Surface Coal Mining Land Conservation & Reclamation Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
62 Illinois Administrative Code 1700-1850
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Certification is required for those individuals who are directly responsible for blasting operations conducted at surface coal mining operations. Certificates are valid for 5 years. <P>

Failure to comply with the law or rules may result in suspension or revocation of the blaster's certification.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file an "Application for Blaster Examination and Certification Form", provide a statement from applicant's employer (or other person having personal knowledge of the applicant's blasting experience) that the applicant has had 2 years blasting experience, and proof that the applicant has completed a blaster training course. <P>

Applications are usually processed within 45 day. Applications may be denied (or Certificates may be revoked) if an individual has been convicted of a felony or has been a patient in a mental institution within the past 5 years. Applicants also must pass a written exam. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Following issuance of certification, the blaster is obligated to adhere to all federal and state regulations. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

