<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Certificate for Storage of Explosives</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Certificate for Storage of Explosives
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Office of Mines & Minerals<BR>
Explosives Division<BR>
503 East Main Street<BR>
Benton, Illinois 62812<BR>
(618) 439-4320<BR>
TDD:  (217) 524-4626<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 3000, 3002 (Illinois Explosives Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
62 Illinois Administrative Code 200.200-301
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
No one  may possess or store explosive materials without a certificate from the Office of Mines and Minerals (OMM). An individual holding an Explosives license is exempted from this requirement so long as the amount of explosives purchased is used on that same day.  The purpose of Certification of explosives storage is to ensure proper construction of storage magazines and proper precautions are taken prior to storage.  Certificate holders are allowed to store a specific amount of explosives specified by OMM. Certificates expire yearly on February 28. To renew a certificate, a renewal application must be submitted with the required fee at the time of OMM's annual inspection. This inspection is conducted during the 6 months preceding the expiration date.  Failure to comply with requirements of the Act may result in suspension, revocation of a Certificate, refusal to renew a Certificate or other disciplinary action, including fines.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file an "Application For Storage Certificate For Explosive Materials Magazine". If an application is denied, OMM provides written notification stating the grounds for denial. An applicant must reply in writing within 15 days to request a hearing. Failure to provide written request within 15 days, constitutes a waiver of the applicants right to contest the decision. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An applicant must identify a "Magazine Keeper". That person is subject to fingerprinting. Fingerprints must be on file prior to issuance of the Certificate. The certificate holder must maintain records of each transaction where explosive materials are sold, purchased or transferred, and conduct an annual inventory of explosive materials, submitting it to an Explosives Division Inspector or to the Explosives Division. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<PRE>
Amt. of Explosive Material:	Amt. of Blasting Agents:	 No. of Blasting Caps:<P>

1 - 50 lbs	    $25         1-50,000 lbs        $100    1-1,000          $25
51 - 1,000	    $50         50,001-300,000 lbs  $200    1,001-50,000     $100
1,001 - 50,000      $100        50,000+             $200    50,001- 300,000  $200
</PRE>

Renewal fees are the same as original application fees.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
