<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Game Breeding and Hunting Preserve Area License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<H3>I.    Business Requirement Profile:
    </H3><DL><DD>
Game Breeding and Hunting Preserve Area License
                 </DD></DL><HR><H3>
II.  Agency:                       </H3>
                                        <DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Conservation Division                       <BR>
Commercial Permits                              <BR>
P. O. Box 19458                                     <BR>
Springfield, IL 62794-9458                              <BR>
(217) 785-3423                                              <BR>
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
III. Statute:     </H3>
                       <DL><DD>
520 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/3.27 to 3.35.
                               </DD></DL><H3>
Regulation:                                  </H3><DL><DD>

17 Illinois Administrative Code 745.</DD></DL><HR><H3>

IV.  Requirement Description:                         </H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required before any individual, association, club or corporation may operate a Game Breeding and Hunting Preserve Area.

Before issuing a license, the Department conducts a field evaluation of the proposed area to determine that it satisfies DONR requirements for public safety and size (an area may consist of not more than 1280, nor less than 200, contiguous acres, of  which 100 acres must be suitable wildlife habitat).  

Licenses are issued for a period of  up to one year and are valid from May 1 of the year issued, and expire the following April 30.
        </DD></DL><HR><H3>
V.   Approval Process:    </H3>
                               <DL><DD>
Applicant must complete and file with the Department a "Wildlife Resources - Game Breeding and Hunting Preserve" application together with the applicable fee.  Upon receipt of a completed application and fee, the Department schedules a field evaluation.  Any problems established by the Department's application review or field evaluation are brought to the attention of applicant who is allowed an opportunity to correct them.  

Applications are denied if the area does not qualify in terms of size or suitable habitat or if public safety problems are not or cannot be corrected.

Applications must be filed with the Department prior to July 1 of the year of intended use.
                                       </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites:    </H3>
                                                              <DL><DD>
The Department requires licensed areas to be posted. Operators are obliged to release a minimum of 250 pheasant or quail seasonally (between September 1 and April 15). License holders must maintain records of information, including the number of hunter-trips, a description of species "harvested", a log of all hunter's license numbers and city of residence, the number of birds released in the area and the dates they were released.  Records must be forwarded to the Department at the end of each month. 

Contact the Department for a complete description of operating and reporting requirements.
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
VII. Fees:        </H3>
                       <DL><DD>
$100 License fee.              <P>

Make checks or money orders payable to the Department of Natural Resources.
                                  </DD></DL>






<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

