<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Migratory Waterfowl Hunting Area Permit   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
<h3>I.    Business Requirement Profile:</h3><dl><dd>
Migratory Waterfowl Hunting Area Permit             </DD></DL><HR><H3>

II.  Agency:</H3><DL><DD>     Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
               Conservation Division         <BR>
               Migratory Waterfowl Permits       <BR>
               P. O. Box 19458                       <BR>
               Springfield, IL 62794-9458                <BR>
               (217) 785-3423                                <BR>
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
III. Statute:  </H3><DL><DD>520 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/3.6 to 3.8.
          </DD></DL><H3>Regulation:</H3><DL><DD>  17 Illinois Administrative Code 590
                                                </DD></DL><HR><H3>
IV.  Requirement Description: </H3><DL><DD>A Permit is required for any person who controls land or water (or both) for commercial purposes, for the taking of wild ducks or geese, or for the privilege of taking wild ducks or geese.  (For purposes of this permit, a person is considered to be in "commercial" control of land or water if he or she receives compensation directly or indirectly in exchange for the opportunity to enter onto that land or water.)  

Migratory Waterfowl Hunting Area Permits are issued by the Department on the basis of principal use (that is, ducks or geese), and entitle permit holders to harvest either wild ducks or wild geese.  

Permits are valid from the first day of the season during which it is lawful to take migratory waterfowl, and expire each year with the last day of the season.
                                           </DD></DL><HR><H3>
V.   Approval Process:</H3><DL><DD>  Applicants must file a "Migratory Waterfowl Hunting Area Permit Application" with the Department, together with appropriate fees, payable by check or money order to the Illinois Department of Natural Resources. Applicants must declare under penalty of perjury that the information on the application is true and accurate, and authorize the Department to verify all statements.

The Department issues permits approximately 1 week after receiving completed applications and fees.
                                   </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post Requisites:</H3><DL><DD>  Applications are made subject to the provisions of Chapter 61, Wildlife Code, the Federal "Migratory Bird Treaty Act" and the "Migratory Bird Hunting Stamp Act".
                                                                  </DD></DL>  <HR><H3>
VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
$15 for each blind or pit.<P> Make check or money order payable to Department of Natural Resources.
                             </DD></DL>






