<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Permit for Drilling or Converting a Well for Class II Injection purposes</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Permit for Drilling or Converting a Well for Class II Injection purposes
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Office of Mines & Minerals<BR>
Oil & Gas Division<BR>
524 South Second Street<BR>
Springfield, IL 62701-1787<BR>
(217) 782-7756<BR>
TDD:  (217) 524-4626<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statute 725/6
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
62 Illinois Administrative Code 240 C
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Permit must be obtained from the Department of Natural Resources prior to drilling or converting a well for Class II injection purposes, or commencing injection into a well converted for injection purposes. <P>

Failure to obtain a permit prior to drilling, converting or operating a Class II well will result in enforcement action, including a civil penalty.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit a "A Class II Injection Well Permit Application", Form #OG-3 together with all information requested on the back of the form, proof of public notice (publishing notice in a newspaper in the county where the proposed well will be located), and notice to offset operators. <P>

Class II injection wells must be constructed and operated in accordance with Department rules and cannot be located within 200 feet of a potable water well or within 2500 feet of a municipal water well.<P>

If an objection is received, DNR may hold a hearing to resolve the objection. Review, approval and permit issuance generally takes approximately 30 to 60 days depending upon whether any additional information is required by DNR. <P>

Department decisions are subject to administrative review.   <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A  $2,500 Individual or Blanket $25,000; $50,000 or $100,000 Bond is required for new operators. <P>

Applicants must file a "Well Completion Report", form #OG-9, and may be required to file a "Well Drilling Report", form #OG-5; an "Annual Class II Well Report", form #OG-18; a "Tubing and Packer Report", form #OG-13, and "Mechanical Integrity Test", form #OG-23 prior to injection and at least once every 5 years, and; "Temporary Abandonment", form #OG-15 if the well is to be temporarily abandoned. <P>

Submission of logs to the State Geological Survey, also may be required. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A non-refundable application fee of $100 is required.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
