<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Permit for Construction & Operation of a Storage Structure for Class II Fluids</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Permit for Construction & Operation of a Storage Structure for Class II Fluids
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Natural Resources<BR>
Office of Mines & Minerals (OMM)<BR>
Oil & Gas Division<BR>
524 South Second Street<BR>
Springfield, IL 62701-1787<BR>
(217) 782-7756<BR>
TDD:  (217) 524-4626<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 725/6
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
62 Illinois Administrative Code 240 H 850
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An application must be submitted to OMM before construction may begin on a concrete storage structure for the temporary storage of produced water. <P>

Failure to obtain a permit for construction of a Class II Fluid Structure prior to commencing construction may result in enforcement action, including civil penalties. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit a "Concrete Storage Structure Application", form #OG-11 to OMM. The application must be completed and signed by the applicant and a State Well Inspector who has inspected the proposed site.  <P>

A schematic diagram showing the complete construction of the proposed structure is also required.  <P>

Review, approval and permit issuance generally takes 3 to 5 days.  Department decisions are subject to administrative review. <P>

Structures cannot be located with 200 feet of an existing inhabited structure (except under certain conditions), a domestic water supply a well, stream, body of water or marshy land (except under certain conditions), within 2500 feet of a municipal water supply well or in an area subject to annual flooding by streams, rivers, lakes or drainage ditches. Pits must be maintained in a leak free condition and netted to prevent birds from landing in the structure.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
