<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Accreditation of persons performing Medical Radiation Technology
Procedures.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Accreditation of persons performing Medical Radiation Technology
Procedures.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL>
<DD>Illinois Department of Nuclear Safety<BR>
Office of Radiation Safety / Division of Electronic Products<BR>
1035 Outer Park Dr.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62704<BR>
(217) 785-9913<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
420 Illinois Compiled Statutes 40/5.  The Radiation Protection Act of 1990.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 32, Illinois Administrative Code, Part 401.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Persons who perform medical radiation procedures on humans (including
radiography, nuclear medicine or radiation therapy procedures, such as
adiographers, Limited Radiographers, Chiropractic Radiographers, Nuclear
Medicine Technologists, Radiation Therapists) must be accredited, or
exempted from accreditation, by the Department.  There are four types of
Accreditation:  Active, Temporary, Conditional & Accreditation in Limited
Radiography. Persons and employers who act in violation of accreditation
requirements are subject to civil penalties.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file Form # IL 473-0180 together with proof that the
applicant has met the requirements for initial accreditation, or renewal of
accreditation.   Applications usually are processed in 10 working days.
Qualified applicants will be accredited to perform medical radiation
procedures within a specifically defined scope of practice.  Denied
applications may be appealed to the Department. <P>  
</DD></DL>

<HR>     
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Active Accreditation is valid for 2 years, and requires proof that the
applicant has passed the required registry or board certification
examination. Renewal requires 24 hours of continuing education approved by
the Department.<P>

Conditional Accreditation, based on experience only is no longer issued.
Persons previously issued conditional accreditation may renew the
accreditation for 2 year periods by completing 24 hours of continuing
education acceptable to the Department.<P>

Temporary Accreditation is valid for 2 years (and is not renewable)
requires proof of graduation from an approved training program and
eligibility for the registry or board certification exam. Accreditation in
Limited Radiography  requires proof that applicant has passed an
examination acceptable to the Department for limited radiography.  Limited
radiography accreditation must be issued in one or more categories of
Chest, Extremities, Spine, or Skull, as qualified by examination.  Limited
radiography accreditation is issued for 2 year periods and is renewable
provided the applicant has achieved 12 hours of continuing education
acceptable to the Department during the previous 24 months of
accreditation.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG><EM>Application Fees (Initial or Renewal): </EM></STRONG> $40.00<P>
<STRONG><EM>Limited Radiography Testing Fee: </EM></STRONG>       $30.00
</DD></DL>

<HR>
