<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Architects</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Architects
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section, Design Unit<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786	<BR>
Phone (217) 785-0877<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 305/1-40 Illinois Architecture Practice Act
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter VII, subchapter b, Part 1150
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required to offer architectural services. Providing Architectural services without a License is a Class A misdemeanor for the first offense and a Class 4 felony for subsequent offenses. (Each day of practicing architecture, and each day of attempting or offering to practice architecture without a license constitutes a separate offense.)<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application forms are available from the Department have both an examination application and application for license. Applications are reviewed by the Illinois Architect Licensing Board for recommendation on eligibility to take the written exam. Approved applicants are notified that they may register to be scheduled for the exam. <P>

Denial of eligibility to take the exam is usually based on deficiencies in education or experience. Reconsideration may be requested within 35 days of the date of the denial notice. Denials may also be appealed through Judicial Review by filing suit in the appropriate circuit court. <P>

Once the exam is successfully completed, application for License may be made to the Department. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicant must have a five or six year professional degree in architecture from an accredited program or a program approved by the Department.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Application for License							$100.<P>
Certificate of License							$ 20.<P>
Duplicate License								$ 20.<P>
Renewal of License:								$ 60.<P>
License as an architecture corporation/partnership:	$ 75.<P>
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
