<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Optometrist, Ancillary Office of Optometry, Registration for use of Topical Ocular Pharmaceutical agents (Individual and branch office)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Optometrist, Ancillary Office of Optometry, Registration for use of Topical Ocular Pharmaceutical agents (Individual and branch office)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Health Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786<BR>
(217) 524-7540<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 80/1-29
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code Chapter VII, Subchapter b, Part 1320
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required to practice optometry.  Licensed 	Optometrists must apply to the Department for a certificate of registration to use topical ocular pharmaceutical agents, as defined by the Department for examination purposes.  <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must be U.S. citizens who have graduated from a program of optometry education approved by the Department and must pass a written examination. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants are eligible to take the written examination once they have graduated from an approved program of Optometry education.  Applicants for topical ocular registration must have received pharmacological training and certification from an accredited institution of higher education. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Registered Optometrist: $250<P>
Registered Ancillary:  $100<P>
Registered Topical Ocular:   $150<P>
Topical Ocular Branch:  $50<P>
Continuing Education Sponsor:  $500<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
