<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Pharmacist and Pharmacy Practice </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Pharmacist and Pharmacy Practice 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Health Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786<BR>
(217) 524-7540<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 85/1-39 
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
69 Illinois Administrative Code, Chap VII, Subchapter B, Part 1330
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required to practice Pharmacy or to operate a pharmacy in Illinois.  Pharmacies are licensed according to the pharmaceutical services they offer. The Department issues pharmacy Licenses by division I through V: <P>
<DL><DD>
Division I pharmacies offer pharmacy services to the general public. <P>

Division II pharmacies offer pharmacy services primarily to hospitals and nursing home facilities but are not physically located within those facilities.<P>

Division III pharmacies are located within a hospital or nursing home facility.<P>

Division IV pharmacies offer for sale radioactive pharmaceuticals. <P>

Division V are pharmacies holding a Division II or III which also provide services to the general 	public.<P>
</DD></DL>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for a pharmacist License must be a graduate from a first professional degree program with at least 5 academic years, have completed a program of practice in a pharmacy under the direct supervision of a registered pharmacist, and pass a written examination approved by the Department.  <P>

Application forms are available from the Department by written request or by calling the Forms Unit at (217) 785-0842. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
All Licensed Pharmacies must have a designated "Pharmacist in Charge". The name of this individual must appear on the Pharmacy license and he/she will be responsible for all aspects of the operation related to the practice of pharmacy. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Pharmacist application fee:  $75.<P> 
Pharmacy license fee:  $100.<P>
Fee for a Pharmacy to change its designated Pharmacist-in-Charge:  $25.00.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
