<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Physical Therapist & Physical Therapist Assistant </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Physical Therapist & Physical Therapist Assistant 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Health Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786<BR>
(217) 524-7540<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 90/1-36
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code Chapter VII, Subchapter b, Part 1340
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required to engage in the treatment of physical disability or promoting the physical fitness and well being of other persons through the use of therapeutic exercise, therapeutic massage, and the use of the effective properties of heat, cold, light, water, radiant energy, electricity, sound, and air. <P>

Separate licenses are issued for Physical Therapists and Assistant Therapists.<P> 

Licensed Assistant Therapists must work under the direct supervision of a licensed Physical Therapist.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for Physical Therapist and Therapist Assistant must be at least 18 years old, have graduated from an approved educational program, and pass a written examination approved by the Department. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Prior to taking the examination, applicants must complete a curriculum in Physical Therapy approved by the Department. Applicants for Physical Therapy Assistant must complete a curriculum in physical therapy, consisting of a 2 year college level program. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Physical Therapist:	 			$25.<BR>
Assistant Physical Therapist:		$25.<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
