<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Private Alarm Contractor, Private Alarm Contractor Agency, Private Alarm Contractor Agency Branch Office</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Private Alarm Contractor, Private Alarm Contractor Agency, Private Alarm Contractor Agency Branch Office
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786	<BR>
Phone (217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes  446/1-29
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter VII, Subchapter b
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A license is required for any person or business to sell, install, monitor, maintain, alter, repair, replace, service, or respond to alarm systems, including fire alarm systems, at protected premises or at premises to be protected on an emergency basis and not as a full-time security guard. <P>

Persons, firms, associations or corporations that engage in the private alarm contractor business and employ one or more persons in the business must have a License for a Private Alarm Agency.  <P>

(This license is not required for persons or firms that only manufacture or sell alarm systems.)<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License application forms are available from the Department. <P>

Applicants for Private Alarm Contractor must pass a written exam approved by the Department.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Prerequisites, Co-Requisites, & Post Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for Private Alarm Contractors must be 21, U.S. citizens and have at least three years experience, of the five years preceding the date of application, working as a manager or administrator for an agency licensed by the Department as a Private Alarm Contractor Agency. Appropriate education may be applied toward the experience requirement  Also, applicants must obtain liability insurance in the amount of $1 million.  <P>

Applicants must show proof of this insurance before a license will be issued. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Private Security Alarm Contractor - $500.<P>
Private Security Alarm Contractor Agency - $500.<P>
Private Security Alarm Contractor Agency (Branch Office) - $200.<P>
Agency Employee - $55.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
