<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Professional Counselor and Clinical Professional Counselor Licensing   </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>
 <H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile: 
 </H3><DL><DD>License for Professional Counselor and Clinical Professional Counselor Licensing   
              </DD></DL><HR><H3>
II.  Agency:</H3><DL><DD>     Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
               Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
               Health Services Section         <BR>
               320 West Washington, 3rd Floor      <BR>
               Springfield, Illinois 62786             <BR>
               (217) 524-7540                              <BR>
</DD></DL><HR><H3>
III.      Statute:</H3><DL><DD>    225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 107/1-170
                               </DD></DL><H3>
          Regulation:  </H3><DL><DD>    68 Illinois Administrative Code VII, Subchapter b, Part 1375
                                    </DD></DL><HR><H3>
IV.  Requirement Description: </H3><DL><DD>A Professional Counselor license is required for anyone offering services to assist persons in coping with life issues such as relationships, conflicts, problem solving, decision making, and developmental concerns. 

A Clinical Professional Counselor license is required for anyone providing professional counseling services and mental health services. This includes but is not limited to, the application of clinical counseling theory and techniques to prevent and alleviate mental and emotional disorders and psychopathology and to promote optimal mental health, rehabilitation, treatment, testing, assessment, and evaluation.
                                           </DD></DL><HR><H3>
V.   Approval Process: </H3><DL><DD>Successful completion of an Department approved written examination is required for both Professional Counselor and Clinical Professional Counselor.  Separate exams are given for each license.
                                    </DD></DL><HR><H3>
VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites: </H3><DL><DD><STRONG>Professional Counselor</STRONG> - Applicants for both Professional Counselor and Clinical Professional Counselor must be at least 21 years of age. Applicants must hold a Master's or Doctoral degree  counseling, rehabilitation counseling , or psychology. Candidates without a Masters or Doctoral degree must have completed a baccalaureate degree in a human service field in combination with 5 years of full-time supervised counseling experience. 

<P><STRONG>Clinical Professional Counselor </STRONG>- All applicants must meet one of the following education and experience requirements.<ol><LI> Hold a Master's degree in counseling, rehabilitation counseling, psychology (or a similar program approved by the  Department) in combination with 2 years of full-time satisfactory supervised employment working as a clinical professional counselor subsequent to earning the Master's degree or<P><LI> Hold a Doctoral degree in counseling, rehabilitation counseling, psychology (or other Department approved program) in combination with 2 years of full-time satisfactory supervised employment working as a clinical professional counselor with 1 of the 2 required years subsequent to earning the Doctoral degree.<P></OL>
                                                                   </DD></DL>  <HR><H3>
VII.      Fees:
                 </H3><DL><DD>
Professional Counselor (Temporary) - $150.<BR>
Professional Counselor - $150.                <BR>
Clinical Professional Counselor (Temporary) - $150. <BR>
Clinical Professional Counselor - $150                  <BR>
                                                            </DD></DL>






