<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Professional Engineer, Structural Engineer, Certificate for Engineer Intern</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Professional Engineer, Structural Engineer, Certificate for Engineer Intern
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section, Design Unit<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786	<BR>
(217) 785-0877<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. 	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 325/1- 49  & 340/1-38.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Professional Engineer license is required to use knowledge of mathematical and natural sciences to make determinations affecting the planning, design and selection of materials and methods to be used in, and administration of construction contracts for, or site observation of an engineering system or facility, where the consultation, conception, investigation, evaluation, planning, design, selection, administration, or observation requires extensive knowledge of engineering laws, formulae, materials, practice and construction methods. <P>

Applicants for a license must first be registered as an Engineer Intern.  Students with a bachelors degree in Engineering must contact the Department and seek registration as an Engineer Intern. <P>

A Structural Engineering license is required for persons using engineering data and scientific principles to calculate loads and stresses on and the size and strength of component parts of structures with foundations, columns, girders, trusses, arches and beams as  essential features.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Engineer Intern</EM> applicants must have a bachelors degree from an approved program (or be in the last semester of an approved program) or have completed a non-approved curriculum and show evidence of 4 years engineering experience. <P>

<EM>Professional Engineer</EM> applicants must have a bachelors degree from an approved curriculum with 4 years experience in engineering, or a graduate from a non-approved curriculum with 8 years engineering work experience.  (Advanced degrees in engineering may be substituted for work experience requirements.)<P>

<EM>Structural Engineer</EM> applicants must have a bachelors degree from an approved engineering curriculum and 4 years experience in structural engineering, or a bachelors degree in an approved related science curriculum and 8 years experience in structural engineering. <P>

Candidates with these qualifications may apply to the Department to take the written exam required for issuance for an Engineer Intern, Professional Engineer or Structural Engineer license.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Licenses:Engineer Intern: $20<P>
Professional Engineer: $100<P>
Structural Engineer: $100<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
