<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: License for Professional Nurse and Practical Nurse</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Professional Nurse and Practical Nurse
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Health Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786<BR>
(217) 524-6731<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 65/1-49
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code, Chapter VII, Subchapter B, Part 1300.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required to engage in the practice of professional nursing, either as a Registered Professional Nurse or a Licensed Practical nurse. <P>

Licensure allows Practical Nurses to perform acts to care for the ill or injured selected by and performed under the direction of a registered professional nurse. <P>

Professional Nurse licenses allow the holder to perform any nursing act in the evaluation and care for the ill, prevention of illness in others, administration of medications and treatments prescribed by licensed physicians, dentists, or podiatrists. Professional Nurses also may perform supervision or teaching of nursing skills which require specialized skill.<P>

Licenses are valid for two years and may be renewed.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for a Practical Nurse License must have completed a Practical Nursing  program of  not less than 1 year academic year, and must pass a written exam approved by the Department.<P>

Applicants for a Professional Nurse License must have graduated from a Professional Nursing program of not less than 2 academic years in length and pass a written examination approved by the Department. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License for Registered Professional Nurse (RN) 	$50<P>
License for Licensed Practical Nurse (LPN)  	$50<P>
License renewals					$40<P>
Temporary Permit					$25<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
