<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration as a Medical Service Corporation</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I. 	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration as a Medical Service Corporation
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II. 	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section<BR>
320 West Washington, 3rd Floor<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62786	<BR>
(217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
805 Illinois Compiled Statutes 15/1-18
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration with the Department is required before any person may operate a Medical Service Corporation for the study, diagnosis, treatment of human ailments and injuries and promote medical, surgical, and scientific research and knowledge. A certificate of registration from the Department is required before a corporation may be formed for that purpose. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The Department will issue a Certificate of Registration for a Medical Service Corporation if the incorporators, officers, directors, and shareholders are licensed physicians under the Medical Practice Act of 1987 and have no disciplinary action pending against any of them.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The Department requires proof that the incorporators, shareholders, and directors of the proposed medical corporation are licensed physicians. Corporations organized under this act may bear the last name of one or more persons formerly or currently associated with it. Also, a name not including the surname of any present or former shareholder may be used, provided that name and a list of the shareholders is registered with the recorder of the county in which the corporation is located. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Medical Service Corporation:	$50<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
