<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration for Barbers, Barber Teachers, and Licensure for Barber Schools</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration for Barbers, Barber Teachers, and Licensure for Barber Schools
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Department of Professional Regulation<BR>
Licensing & Testing Division<BR>
Professional Services Section<BR>
Phone (217) 785-0894<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 410/1-1 et seq. The Illinois Barber, Cosmetology, Esthetics and Nail Technology Act
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 68 Illinois Administrative Code Chapter VII, subchapter b Part 1175
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Barbers and Barber Teachers must meet education and exam requirements and must  be registered with the Department.   A License is required to operate a Barber School. Operating as a Barber, Barber Teacher, or a Barber School without a Certificate or License is a Class B misdemeanor for the first offense, Class A misdemeanor for the second offense and a Class 4 Felony for each subsequent offense.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A written exam for Barbers and Barber Teachers. Applications are reviewed by a testing service before candidates may take the exam. After passing the exam, applicants will receive application forms for a license. <P>

Denial of eligibility to take the exam is usually based on deficiencies in education or experience.<P>

Reconsideration may be requested within 35 days of the date of the denial notice by submitting additional or mitigating information. Denials may also be appealed to the circuit court. <P>

Barber School Licenses may be issued only after an on-site inspection of the proposed school site.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Barbers:</EM> Must be at least 16, high school graduates or GED equivalents, graduates from an approved school of barbering and completed a total of 1500 hours in the study of barbering over not less than 9 months.  <P>

Barber Teachers must be at least 18, have graduated from high school and be a registered Barber and have graduated from an approved Barber School with a curriculum of 500 hours in barber teacher training and 3 years of practical experience as a registered Barber, or have completed a curriculum of 1,000 hours of barber teaching. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
	Application for Licensure:			$ 25.<P>
	Renewal of License:					$ 40.<P>
	License Restoration & Lapsed Renewal:	$ 10.<P>
	Duplicate License					$ 20.<P>
	Certification of License:			$ 20.<P>
	Barber School License Fee:			$100.<P>

These fees are in addition to any examination fees.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
