<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Ambulance Services</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.    Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Ambulance Services
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.   Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>  
Office of Health Care Regulation <BR>
Division of Emergency Medical Services and Highway Safety<BR>
525 West Jefferson<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 785-2080<BR>
TDD:  800-547-0466 (hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
210 Illinois Compiled Statutes 50  (The Emergency Medical Services (EMS) Systems Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 535 (Emergency Medical Services Code)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The purpose of this license requirement is to assure public safety by requiring that ambulances meet all safety requirements and have proper equipment.  A license  is required before an ambulance vehicle may furnish, operate, conduct, maintain or advertise services. Licensure requirements address the number and qualifications of personnel; vehicle design and equipment; and operational requirements. Operating in violation of these requirements may cause a license to be suspended and result in fines of up to $10,000.<P> 

Licenses are valid for 1 year.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.   Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file with the Department an "Application for Licensure as an Ambulance Service Provider".  Upon receipt of an application, the Department will schedule an inspection.<P> 

If an application for license is denied for reasons such as a lack of proper equipment or improper communication devices, the applicant may correct the deficiencies and reapply.<P> 

Applications to renew a license must be filed with the Department at least 60 days prior to expiration to schedule an inspection. After the renewal inspection, license applications generally take 2 weeks to process.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.   Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
