<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Asbestos Abatement Contractor License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Asbestos Abatement Contractor License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Office of Health Protection<BR>
Asbestos Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-3517<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
105 Illinois Compiled Statutes 105/1 et seq. (Asbestos Abatement Act); P.A. #89-143 (Commercial and Public Buildings Asbestos Abatement Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 855.50 C and 855 Appendix C, Illustration E (Application for Contractor  License)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Asbestos abatement contractors in public and private schools (grades 1-12) and commercial and public buildings must be licensed by the Department. Work requiring a license includes removal, enclosure, and encapsulation of building materials containing asbestos. Only contractors with experience in conducting asbestos abatement or those who employ an experienced asbestos project supervisor are eligible for a license.<P> 

Licensed contractors failing to comply with license requirements are subject to a Class A Misdemeanor.  Licenses expired for less than 2 years may be reinstated by the Department.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for a license must submit:  1.  A list of three character references from former employers, 2. Certification of financial responsibility documenting liability insurance, self insurance, group insurance, group self-insurance, a letter of credit, or a bond in the amount of at least $500,000 ($1,000,000 for work in commercial and public buildings), 3.  Evidence of successful completion of an initial contractor or supervisor training course which is approved by the Department, the USEPA or by another state,  4.  Evidence that the contractor's asbestos workers have an asbestos worker license, 5.  A list of prior contracts for asbestos abatement projects, including dates, names, addresses, and telephone numbers of building owners for whom the projects were performed,  6.  Application for licensure as an asbestos abatement contractor.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Contractor's must have a minimum of 1 year experience in asbestos abatement. A new contractor is eligible if employer references show a minimum of 1 year experience in asbestos abatement project supervision or by employing a supervisor with the same. Contractors must be able to show the results of air monitoring performed during previous asbestos abatement projects in accordance with federal Occupational Safety and Health Administration regulations, and evidence of final air monitoring results from 10 asbestos abatement projects conducted by the contractor or supervised by a licensed supervisor employed by the contractor.  Contractors must maintain with the Department a current certificate of financial responsibility.  Contractors must also notify the Department of changes in the status of the certificate, including expiration, renewal, or alteration of terms. A current certificate of insurance  must be filed with the Department by May 1 each year. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG>An initial review fee:</STRONG> $250.<P> 
<STRONG>License fee:</STRONG> $500.<P> 
<STRONG>Annual Renewal Fee:</STRONG> $500<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
