<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Asbestos Abatement Project Supervisor's License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Asbestos Abatement Project Supervisor's License
</DD></DL> 

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Office of Health Protection<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Asbestos Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-3517<BR>   
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
105 Illinois Compiled Statutes 105/1 et seq. (Asbestos Abatement Act) and P.A. # 89-143 (Commercial and Public Building's Asbestos Abatement Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 855.40, 855.55 and 855 Appendix C, Illustration D.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An asbestos supervisor license is required to supervise asbestos abatement projects for public and private schools (grades 1 - 12) and commercial and public buildings. The purpose of the license is to ensure that persons supervising asbestos abatement projects are qualified.  License holders failing to comply with the Code are subject to fines which range with the severity of the violation.<P> 

Licenses are valid for 1 year and expire May 15 of each year. Licenses issued after January 15 expire May 15 of the following year.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file an application for licensure as an Asbestos Abatement Project Supervisor; two 1x1" photos, evidence of a current Department Asbestos Worker License, certification of successfully passing a Contractor/Supervisor Training course and, if the initial course certificate has expired, all Contractor/Supervisor Refresher Course certificates. The Department will process the application within 60 days.<P>
 
Denied applications may be revised and resubmitted after all requirements have been satisfied. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must have a current Department Asbestos Worker License and have successfully completed a Contractor / Supervisor Initial Course. <P>

License holders must successfully complete an annual one-day asbestos supervisor refresher course.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG>Application fee:</STRONG> $50.<P>

<STRONG>Renewals applications:</STRONG> $50. <P>

A $15 late fee is required if the renewal application is not received by May 1.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

