<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Asbestos - Air Sampling Professional's License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Asbestos - Air Sampling Professional's License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Office of Health Protection<BR>
Asbestos Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-3517<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
105 Illinois Compiled Statutes 105/1 et seq. (Asbestos Abatement Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 855.40, 855.260, and 855 Appndx C, Illustr. F
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:  </H3>
<DL><DD>
Air monitoring for asbestos abatement projects conducted in a public or non-public school building (grades 1-12) must be done by a Department-licensed air sampling professional. The purpose of the license is to assure that air monitoring during asbestos abatement projects for school buildings are done by properly qualified individuals. Failure to comply with code requirements is a Class A Misdemeanor. Licenses are valid for 1 year, and expire on May 15 each year. Licenses issued after January 15 expire May 15 of the following year.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process: </H3> 
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file an application for licensure as an Asbestos Air Sampling Professional; two 1x1" photos; proof of a Bachelor's Degree in life, environmental or physical sciences or in engineering. Certified industrial hygienists may, in lieu of a degree, submit their American Board of Industrial Hygienist Certificate. Applicants must submit written verification of 520 hours on-site experience in general indoor air pollution sampling or, in lieu of a degree, written verification of 2080 hours on-site experience in air sampling for asbestos on abatement projects. The Department processes applications in 60 days. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:  </H3> 
<DL><DD>
Applicants must have at a  minimum 520 hours experience sampling indoor air for pollutants. Applicants must successfully complete the National Institute of Occupational Safety and Health (NIOSH) training course #582, titled "Sampling and Evaluating Airborne Asbestos Dust", or a course equivalent in length and content. In lieu of a degree, written verification of 2,080  hours of on-site experience in air sampling for asbestos on abatement projects, is required.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG>License renewal:</STRONG>  $50.<P>
 
A $15.00 additional late fee is assessed for license renewal applications received after May 1.<P>

<STRONG>Reinstatement fee:</STRONG> $15.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
