<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Asbestos Project Designer's License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Asbestos Project Designer's License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Office of Health Protection<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Asbestos Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-3517<BR>
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
105 Illinois Compiled Statutes 105/1 et seq. (Asbestos Abatement Act) and P.A. #89-143 (Commercial and Public Building Asbestos Abatement Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 855.40, 855.360 and 855 Appendix C, Illustration C.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Project Designer License is required to design asbestos abatement projects for public and private schools (grades 1-12) and commercial and public buildings. The purpose of the license is to ensure that persons designing asbestos abatement projects are properly qualified. Failure to comply with the license requirement is a Class A Misdemeanor. Licenses expire May 15 each year. Licenses issued after January 15 expire May 15 the next year.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file an application for licensure as an Asbestos Project Designer; two 1x1" photos, Project Designer Initial Course certificate or Contractor/Supervisor Initial Course certificate only if the course was completed before April 4, 1994, an Inspector and Management Planner Initial Course certificates and current refresher course certificates for the above courses (if the initial course certificates have expired), expired refresher course certificates; a copy of an Illinois Architectural, Professional Engineer, or an Structural Engineer License, or a Certified Industrial Hygienist Certificate. The Department will process an application in 60 days. 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete a Project Designer, Inspector and Management Planner Training Courses. Applicants must be licensed Architects, Professional Engineers, Structural Engineers, or Certified Industrial Hygienists.<P> 

License holders must annually complete one-day project designer, asbestos building inspector and management planner refresher courses. License holders must remain licensed through the Illinois Department of Professional Regulation as a licensed architect, structural engineer, or professional engineer, unless the licensee is a certified industrial hygienist certified through the American Board of Industrial Hygienists.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG>Application fee:</STRONG> $50.<P> 

<STRONG>Renewal fee:</STRONG>  $50.<P>

A $15 late fee will be required if the renewal application is not received by May 1.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
