<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Asbestos Project Manager's License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Asbestos Project Manager's License
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Public Health<BR>
Office of Health Protection<BR>
Division of Environmental Health / Asbestos Program<BR>
525 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62761<BR>
(217) 782-3517<BR>      
TDD:  1-800-547-0466 (for hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
105 Illinois Compiled Statutes 105/1 et seq. (Asbestos Abatement Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
77 Illinois Administrative Code 855.40, 855.260 and  855 Appendix C, Illustration H.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
An Asbestos Project Manager License is required to act as the building owner's representative to oversee asbestos abatement during abatement in public and private schools (grades 1-12). The purpose of the license is to ensure that persons who oversee asbestos abatement projects for school buildings are properly qualified. Licensees violating the Code are subject to fines that vary with the severity of the violation.<P> 

Licenses expire May 15 each year. Licenses issued after January 15 expire May 15 the next year.<P>
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must file an application for licensure as an asbestos project manager; two 1x1", a Contractor/Supervisor Training Course certificate and a current Contractor/Supervisor refresher course certificate if the initial course certificate has expired, all expired Contractor/Supervisor refresher course certificates, written verification of 2080 hours on-site working experience in building construction projects or 520 hours on-site working experience assisting the licensed project manager on asbestos abatement projects. The Department will process the application within 60 days.<P> 

Denied applications may be revised and resubmitted after all requirements have been satisfied.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must successfully complete a Contractor/Supervisor Initial Course and have 2080 hours of on-site working experience in building construction projects or 520 hours on-site working experience assisting the licensed project manager or asbestos abatement projects.<P> 

Licensees must annually complete an approved Asbestos Contractor/Supervisor Training Course and renew the license.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.  Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG>Application fee:</STRONG> $50.<P>

<STRONG>License renewal:</STRONG> $50.<P>

A $15 late fee will be required if the renewal application is not received by May 1.<P>
</DD><DD></DD></DL>

<HR>
