<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Automobile Rental Tax / Automobile Rental Use Tax (Out-of-State Renters)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:	</H3>
<DL><DD>Automobile Rental Tax (ART)<BR> 
Automobile Rental Use Tax (Out-of-State Renters)</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Central Registration Division<BR>
(217) 785-3707</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:  </H3>
<DL><DD>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes, 155/1</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation: </H3>
<DL><DD>Title 86 Administrative Code, Section 190.101.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:  </H3>
<DL><DD><P>The Automobile Rental Tax and the Rental Use Tax impose a tax upon persons engaged in the business of renting automobiles for a period of one year or less. (A typical example of applications of the Automobile Rental Tax and Automobile Rental Use Tax is an out-of-state rental car business renting to an in-state rentor, or an in-state rentor renting automobiles in Illinois to persons for a term of one year or less.)

<P>Upon registration with the Department, a certificate is issued which authorizes a business to collect and remit Automobile Rental Tax.  Conducting business without a certificate, or failure to collect and remit these taxes, is a Class A Misdemeanor, and may result in penalties including, but not limited to: A tax lien against property, garnishment of wages and bank accounts, revocation of professional licenses, civil judgments, revocation of business certificates of registration, withholdings of state warrants, seizure and sale of assets, nonrenewable of corporate charter and criminal prosecution.

<P>A certificate of registration is valid for 5 years.  The Department will automatically renew a certificate to businesses that have remained in compliance.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Applicants must complete and file a Illinois Business Taxpayer Registration Application (NUC-1A).  The average processing time for the application is 3 weeks.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Certificate holders must file a annual reports ART-1 / ART-2.  A Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) may be required.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>There is no fee for a certificate of registration.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
