<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Business Income Tax (BIT)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:	</H3>
<DL><DD>Business Income Tax (BIT)</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Central Registration Division<BR>
(217) 785-3707<BR></DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:  </H3>
<DL><DD>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes, 5/201 </DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation: </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Income Tax Act, Section 203, Subpart a, b & c.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description: </H3>
<DL><DD><P>Business Income Tax applies to Corporations, Partnerships, and Trusts and Estates conducting business and earning or receiving income in the state of Illinois.  Eligible entities must register with the Department in order to file a Business Income Tax Return.

<P>Failure to register or failure to file Business Income Tax Return is a Class A Misdemeanor, and may result in penalties including, but not limited to: Filing of a tax lien against property, garnishment of wages and bank accounts, recommendation for professional license revocation, civil judgments, revocation of business certificates of registration, withholding of state warrants, seizure and sale of assets, nonrenewal of corporate charter and/or criminal prosecution.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:  </H3>
<DL><DD>To register, an applicant may complete and file with the Department an Illinois Business Taxpayer Registration Application (NUC- 1).  Average processing time is 3 weeks.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites: </H3>
<DL><DD>Reporting Requirements:  Corporations must file an annual report form IL-1120.  Small Businesses must file an annual report form IL-1120ST.  Partnerships must file an annual report form IL-1065.  Trust and Estates must file an annual report form IL 1041.</DD></DL>

<DL><DD>Exempt Corporations must file an annual report form IL-990T.  A Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) number may be required.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>There is no registration fee.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
