<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Cigarette Distributor License</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:	</H3>
<DL><DD>Cigarette Distributor License</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Miscellaneous Taxes Division<BR>
Liquor & Cigarette Review & Correction Section<BR>
(217) 782-7826</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:  </H3>
<DL><DD>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes 130 & 135 </DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation: </H3> 
<DL><DD>86 Illinois Administrative Code 1/440 & 440.5.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:  </H3>
<DL><DD><P>Any one distributing, selling, wholesaling, making or fabricating cigarettes in Illinois, for sale in Illinois, must have a Cigarette Distributor License.  The Cigarette Tax imposed on retailers of cigarettes in Illinois; is prepaid or precollected by distributors by the purchase of stamps, which are affixed to each cigarette package. It is the duty of each distributor to collect the tax from the retailer at or before the time of sale; to affix the required stamps and to remit to the Department the tax collected from retailers.

<P>A Cigarette Distributor License authorizes a business to collect and remit to the Department, taxes due under the Cigarette and Cigarette Use Act.  Anyone acting as a distributor of original packages of cigarettes without a license is guilty of a Class 4 felony.  Anyone possessing cigarettes in original packages not tax stamped, or which are improperly tax stamped is subject to a penalty of $15 for each package of cigarettes in excess of 100 packages.  Licenses are valid for one full year.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process: </H3>
<DL><DD>Applicants must complete and file either Form RC-2 (for corporations) or Form RC-28 (for individual or partnerships), together with a $2,500 surety bond. The average processing time for the application is three weeks.  First-time applicants must provide the Department with letters from three cigarette manufacturers stating that the manufacturers will sell cigarettes to the applicant.  If an application for a license is denied, applicant can petition the Department for a hearing.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Each distributor must file a return (Form RC-6) and supporting schedules on or before the 15th day of each month.  If a business entity changes or a new Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) is issued, that business must re- register and apply for a new Cigarette Distributer License.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>There is a $250 Annual License Fee.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
