<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: County Motor Fuel Tax</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:	</H3>
<DL><DD>County Motor Fuel Tax</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency: </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Central Registration Division<BR>
(217) 785-3707</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute: </H3>
<DL><DD>55 Illinois Compiled Statutes, 5/5-1035.1</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description: </H3>
<DL><DD><P> A County Motor Fuel Tax is imposed upon persons who make retail sales of motor fuel within Kane, McHenry, or DuPage county.  (A typical example of the application of this tax is a service station selling motor fuel to the end user.) Businesses must complete and file with the Department an application for a certificate authorizing collection and remittance of the County Motor Fuel Tax.

<P>Conducting business without a certificate, or failure to collect and remit taxes, is a Class A Misdemeanor, and may result in penalties that include, but are not limited to:  A tax lien against property, garnishment of wages and bank accounts, revocation of professional licenses, civil judgments, revocation of business certificates of registration, withholding of state warrants, seizure and sale of assets, nonrenewal of corporate charter and/or criminal prosecution.

<P>A certificate of registration is valid for 5 years.  If the business remains in compliance, the Department will automatically issue a renewal.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Applicants must complete and file with the Department an Illinois Business Taxpayer Registration Application (NUC-1).  Applications are processed in about 3 weeks.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites: </H3>
<DL><DD>A Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) may be required</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>There is no registration fee.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
