<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Tire User Registration Fee</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
	<DL><DD>Tire User Registration Fee</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>

<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 W. Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Central Registration Division<BR>
(217) 785-3707</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>415 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/55.8.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>

<DL><DD><P> A Tire User Fee is imposed on persons selling tires at retail or for resale, if delivered in Illinois.  Persons selling tires at retail or for resale, that are delivered in Illinois, are required to register with the Department and pay a fee.  Also, wholesalers who sell tires to retailers may voluntarily collect and remit the tire fee on behalf of the retailers.

<P>Conducting business without registering with the Department, or failure to collect and remit these fees, is a Class A Misdemeanor and may result in penalties including, but not limited to the following:  Filing of a tax lien against your property, garnishment of wages and bank accounts, recommendation of professional license revocation, civil judgments, revocation of business certificates of registration, withholding of state warrants, seizure and sale of assets, nonrenewal of corporate charter and/or criminal prosecution.

<P>A certificate of registration gives authority to collect the Tire User Fee for 5 years from the date of its issuance or last renewal if the business is a retailer, or 3 years if the business is a reseller.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD> To register, applicants must complete and file with the Department an Illinois Business Taxpayer Registration Application (NUC- 1).  The average processing time is 3 weeks.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD> To collect and remit the Tire User Fee, a business must be registered for Retailer's Occupation Tax or as a Reseller.  A Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) may be required.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>There is no registration fee.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
