<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Withholding Income Tax Registration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>


<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
	<DL><DD>Withholding Income Tax Registration</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD> Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Central Registration Division<BR>
(217) 785-3707<BR></DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/201, 203.</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>86 Illinois Administrative Code, Section 100.7040.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD><P> Any individual, business or organization that employs any person to perform services must register with the Department and comply with the Registration for Withholding Income Tax requirements.  Registration with the Department authorizes a person or organization to act as a withholding agent.

<P>Conducting business without registering, or failure to collect and remit any and all taxes due, may result in penalties including, but not limited to the following: A tax lien against property, garnishment of wages and bank accounts, recommendation of professional license revocation, Civil judgment, revocation of business certificates of registration, withholdings of state warrants, seizure and sale of assets, nonrenewal of corporate charter and/or criminal prosecution.

<P>A certificate of registration grants authority to collect Withholding Tax and is effective for 5 years from the date of its issuance or last renewal.  If a business remains in compliance, the Department will automatically issue a renewal.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>An applicant must complete and file with the Department an Illinois Business Taxpayer Registration Application (NUC-1).  The average processing time is 3 weeks.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>Reporting Requirements include forms IL-501, IL-941 and W-3 Forms.  A Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) may be required.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>There is no registration fee.</DD></DL>

<HR>
