<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Retailer's Occupation Tax Registration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:	</H3>
<DL><DD>Retailer's Occupation Tax Registration</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency: </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Central Registration Division<BR>
(217) 785-3707</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:  </H3>
<DL><DD>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes, 120/1. </DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation: </H3>
<DL><DD> 86 Illinois Administrative Code, Section 130.101.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:  </H3>
<DL><DD><P>The Retailer's Occupation Tax (commonly referred to as Sales Tax) is imposed on persons or individuals engaged in the business of selling tangible personal property to purchasers for use or consumption.  (A typical example would be a department store selling merchandise to the end user and not for the purpose of resale.)

<P>Retailers must register with the Department to collect and remit Sales Tax.  Conducting business without registering, or failure to collect and remit any taxes due, is a Class A Misdemeanor and may result in penalties including, but not limited to: A tax lien against property, garnishment of wages and bank accounts, recommendation of professional license revocation, civil judgment, revocation of business certificates of registration, withholding of state warrants, seizure and sale of assets, nonrenewal of corporate charter and criminal prosecution.

<P>A certificate of registration grants authority to collect Retailer's Occupation Tax and is effective for 5 years.  If a business remains in compliance, the Department will automatically issue a renewal certificate.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process: </H3>
<DL><DD>An applicant must complete and file with the Department an Illinois Business Taxpayer Registration Application (NUC-1).  The average processing time is 3 weeks.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites: </H3>
<DL><DD>Certificate holders must file annual report forms ST-1, ST-2 & ST-556 (for motor vehicle dealers).  A Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) may be required.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>There is no fee for a certificate of registration.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

