<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Invested Capital Tax Registration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:	</H3>
<DL><DD>Invested Capital Tax Registration</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency: </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Miscellaneous Taxes Division<BR>
Registration & Returns Processing Section<BR>
(217) 782-8750</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD><P>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes 610/1 et. seq.  (Messages Tax Act )
<P>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes 615/2a.1.  (Revenue Tax Act)
<P>35 Illinois Compiled Statutes 620/2a.1 (Public Utilities Revenue Act)</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:  </H3>
<DL><DD><P>An Invested Capital Tax of .8% is imposed upon businesses that sell, supply or furnish water, or businesses that distribute, supply or sell electricity, gas, or telecommunications services.  The tax is applied on the "invested capital"* for the period covered by the annual report filed with the Illinois Commerce Commission (ICC).  In the case of electric or telephone cooperatives, the tax is imposed on the invested capital for the period covered by the annual report filed with the U.S. Department of Agriculture's Rural Electrification Administration (REA).  (*"Invested capital" is an amount equal to the average of the balances at the beginning and end of each taxable period of the taxpayer's total stockholder's equity and total long-term debt, less investments in and advances to all corporations, as set forth on the balance sheets included in the taxpayer's annual report to the ICC.)

<P>Any business regulated by the Illinois Commerce Commission is required to be registered with the Department for the Invested Capital Tax, and to remit tax due according to the Messages Tax Act, Gas Revenue Tax/Act, and the Public Utilities Tax Act.  Failure to file an Invested Capital Tax return, filing a fraudulent return, or willful violation of any provision of this Act, is an offense subject to fines from $750 up to $7,500.  Certificates are not transferable and must be returned to the Department if the business is sold or discontinues.  If the business entity changes or a new Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) is issued, the business needs to re-register and apply for a new license number.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Applicants must complete and file form ICT-7, Invested Capital Tax Application for Registration.  The average processing time for the application is one week.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites: </H3>
<DL><DD>Taxpayers are required to make quarterly estimated payments (25% of the tax liability of the preceding taxable period) using Form ICT-1.  Annual returns are reported on Form ICT-4, and are due on the 15th of the third month following the close of the taxable period.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>There are no registration fees.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
