<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Notice of Sale or Purchase of Business Assets</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Notice of Sale or Purchase of Business Assets
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
Bureau of Collections<BR>
100 W. Randolph<BR>
Chicago, IL 60601<BR>
(312) 814-3063<BR>
TDD (800) 544-5304<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
35 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/902  and 120/5j
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The Illinois Income Tax Act (IITA) and the Retailers Occupation Tax Act (ROTA) impose a liability obligation upon the purchaser of assets* of a business for any unpaid sales, withholding, income, or excise taxes from the seller. This includes returns to be filed for any period up to the close of business, or the sale date. The IITA and ROTA provide for a reporting of a sale. Also, a requirement is imposed on the purchaser to withhold funds from sale proceeds. This acts to limit the amount of transferee liability the purchaser may be held liable for.  A release of transferee liability is issued when the seller's accounts are clear or the purchaser has paid the funds in escrow.<P>  

Purchasing a business without complying with the requirements may result in the seller's unpaid liabilities being transferred to the purchaser.  *(Defined as the major part of  the inventory, furniture and fixtures, machinery and equipment, or real estate.) <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Purchasers of existing businesses must complete a "Notice of Sale\Purchase of Business Assets" (IDOR form # NUC-542-A) available from the Department.<P>  

A common reason for denial is incorrect tax numbers and/or incorrect names supplied by the preparer on the application.<P> 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A copy of the sales contract must be provided to the Department  (A draft copy is acceptable.) The Department must be notified of a change in the date of sale.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
