<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: 1.	 Public Utilities Tax Certificate of Registration (Electric),
2.	Gas Utility Tax Certificate of Registration,
3.	Telecommunications Excise Tax Certificate of Registration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD><P>1.	 Public Utilities Tax Certificate of Registration (Electric),
<P>2.	Gas Utility Tax Certificate of Registration,
<P>3.	Telecommunications Excise Tax Certificate of Registration</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Illinois Department of Revenue<BR>
101 West Jefferson St.<BR>
Springfield, IL 62794<BR>
Taxpayer Services Bureau<BR>
Miscellaneous Taxes Division<BR>
Registration & Returns Processing Section<BR>
(217) 785-5863</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute: </H3>
<DL><DD>(1) 35 Illinois Compiled Statutes (ILCS) 620, (2) 35 ILCS 615, (3) 35 ILCS 630. </DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation: </H3>
<DL><DD>(1) 86 Illinois Admin. Code (IAC) 1/510, (2) 86 IAC 1/470, (3) 86 IAC 495.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:  </H3>

<DL><DD><P>A Certificate of Registration from the Illinois Department of Revenue (Department) is required of any business that must remit taxes imposed by the three following Acts:  (1) Public Utilities Tax Act, (the Public Utilities Tax is imposed on businesses that sell, distribute, supply or furnish electricity for use or consumption and not for resale), (2) Gas Revenue Tax Act, (the Gas Utility Tax is imposed upon businesses that sell, distribute, supply or furnish natural gas for use or consumption and not for resale), and (3) the Telecommunications Excise Tax Act ( the Telecommunications Excise Tax is imposed on businesses that sell, distribute, supply or furnish telecommunications services at retail).

<P>By obtaining a Certificate of Registration, a business becomes properly registered with the Department to collect and remit taxes required by these Acts.  Any taxpayer failing to file a return, or filing a fraudulent return, or willfully violating any provision of these Acts, is guilty of a business offense and upon conviction may be fined from $750 to $7,500.  Certificates are non transferable and must be returned to the Department if the business is sold or discontinued.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>

<DL><DD><P>(1) Applicants for a Public Utilities Tax Certificate of Registration must complete and file Form RPU-3, ("Public Utilities Tax Application for Registration").  

<P>(2) Applicants for a Gas Utility Tax Certificate of Registration must complete and file Form RG-30 ("Gas Revenue Tax Application for Certificate of Registration").  

<P>(3) Applicants for a Telecommunications Excise Tax Certificate of Registration must file a com- pleted Form RT-3 ("Telecommunications Excise Tax Application for Certificate of Registration").  If these businesses have multiple locations, an application must be filed for each location.  The average processing time for these applications is two weeks.  Incomplete applications will be returned.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:  </H3>
<DL><DD>Returns are due monthly unless the Department authorizes quarterly or annual filings.  If a business entity changes, or a new Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) is issued, the business must re-register with the Department and apply for a new license number.</DD></DL>
<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:  </H3>
<DL><DD>There are no fees for a Certificate of Registration.</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
