<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Permit to Organize a Savings and Loan Association</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>


<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Permit to Organize a Savings and Loan Association
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Office of the Commissioner of Savings & Residential Finance<BR>
Thrift Corporate Affairs Division<BR>
205 West Randolph, Suite 1900<BR>
Chicago, Illinois 60606-1811<BR>
(312) 793-1450<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
205 Illinois Compiled Statutes 105\2-1 to 2-9 (Illinois Savings And Loan Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
38 Illinois Administrative Code 1000.110
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Eligibility Criteria:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Any 5 adult Illinois residents may apply for a permit to organize a Savings and Loan Association. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.   Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit to the Commissioner of Savings & Residential Finance (the Commissioner), signed duplicate "Application(s) for a Permit to Organize"; information for the preceding 5 years on each applicant, the present business and a financial statement, the nature and extent of present and prior affiliations with any other financial institutions; exhibits, maps and other data. Applicants must publish a Notice of Intention to Organize in a local newspaper. The Commissioner hears evidence and may investigate and consider all other information. This process usually takes 6-8 weeks. For approval, applications must meet all requirements; assure a reasonable probability of success; show that all withdrawable capital will be insured prior to issuance of a certificate, and; that the name meets certain criteria. Upon submission of the permit application and all information, applicants must form a temporary organization to elect officers, secure subscriptions for capital, adopt articles of incorporation and elect 5 interim directors. The directors organize as a Board and qualify as directors, adopt by-laws, elect officers, collect subscriptions by a bonded individual, obtain and maintain insurance of withdrawable capital by an insurance corporation and, report completion of organization to the Commissioner. A report stating whether all organizational matters are complied with, must be submitted within 12 months or the permit may be revoked and subscriptions refunded. With the report, applicants must submit the names and addresses of all officers and directors, and information on them for the preceding 5 years. This information must include a financial statement and the nature and extent of any prior affiliation with any other financial institutions. Upon organization and submission of the report, the Commissioner examines the affairs of the association. If all information is satisfactory, a Certificate of Complete Organization, authorizing the association to conduct business, is issued. This Certificate must be recorded within 10 days with the articles of incorporation in the office of the county recorder.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-requisites, Co-Requisites, Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must comply with the Savings and Loan and Insurance of Deposit Accounts Acts.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The application processing fee is $1000.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
