<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Real Estate Appraiser License/Certification</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>


<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Real Estate Appraiser License/Certification
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Office of the Commissioner of Savings & Residential Finance<BR>
500 East Monroe, Suite 500<BR>
Springfield, Illinois 62701<BR>
(217) 524-8200<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
225 Illinois Compiled Statutes 455 (Appraiser Certification/License)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
68 Illinois Administrative Code 1455
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Appraiser licensure/certification by the Commissioner is required to conduct business as a Certified General Real Estate Appraiser or a Certified Residential Real Estate Appraiser.  
A License is required to conduct business as a Real Estate Appraiser.  
Licensure and Certification is valid from the date of issue through September 30 of the next odd numbered year, and may be renewed.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete and file with the Commissioner an application for the appropriate certificate or license and pass a written examination.<P>
  
Applications may be denied for cause including forgery, embezzlement, larceny, extortion and moral turpitude felonies.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for Certified REsidential or Certified General Real Estate Appraiser must have 2000 hours experience in specified areas of appraisal and must complete and file an application containing a document form ("LOG-APP") verifying this experience.<P>

Certified General Real Estate Appraiser must have 2000 hours experience (including a minimum of 1000 hours experience in nonresidential real estate) a high school diploma or GED and at least 165 classroom hours of courses in real estate appraisal related subjects, plus 15 classroom hours relating to standards of professional practice from an approved college, community or junior college or a real estate appraisal or trade organization.<P>

Certified Residential Real Estate Appraiser must have 2000 hours experience (including a minimum of 1000 hours experience in residential real estate), a high school diploma or GED and at least 120 classroom hours in subjects related to real estate appraisal,15 hours relating to professional practice standards from an approved college, community or junior college or a real estate appraisal or trade organization.<P>
 
A Licensed Real Estate Appraiser must have a high school diploma or GED and at least 75 classroom hours in subjects related to real estate appraisal, from an approved college, community or junior college or a real estate appraisal or organization.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License application fee:     $100<P>
Certification Application fee:	$150<P>
License Renewal:	$125 per year<P>
Certification renewal: $125 per year<P>

(All fees are in addition to examination or reexamination fees.)<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
