<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Automotive Parts Recyclers, Scrap Processors, Repairers and Rebuilders.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Automotive Parts Recyclers, Scrap Processors, Repairers and Rebuilders.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Office of the Secretary of State of Illinois<BR>
Vehicle Services Department<BR>
Dealer/Remitter Licensing Section<BR>
Howlett Building, Room 069<BR>
Springfield, IL  62756<BR>
(217) 782-7817<BR>
</DD></DL>

<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
615 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/5-301 Illinois Vehicle Code
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 92 Illinois Administrative Code Chapter II, Section 1020.10
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A License is required to conduct the business as an:<P>

Automotive Parts Recycler (The business of acquiring previously owned vehicles and vehicle parts for the primary purpose of disposing of vehicle parts in a manner other than as a scrap processor.<P>

Scrap Processor (A person who purchases a material that may have been a vehicle or essential part of a vehicle for processing into any other form, for remelting purposes only.  No scrap metal processor may sell a vehicle or essential part as such without a license.) <P>

Repairer (A person in the business of returning a vehicle other than one for which a Salvage Certificate has been issued, back to its original or operating condition by restoring, mending, straightening, replacing, altering or painting its "essential parts".)<P>

Rebuilder (A person in the business of returning a vehicle for  which a Salvage Certificate has been issued, back to its original or operating condition.)<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.    Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants for these licenses must complete and file a signed and notarized application with the Secretary.   A separate application is required for each license. Upon receipt of an application the Secretary of State's Police conducts an inspection to assure that the Established Place of Business requirements will be satisfied.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
License holders must maintain records prescribed by the Vehicle Code.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
	<STRONG><EM>Annual Certificate of Authority:</EM> 	</STRONG>			$50.<P>
	<STRONG><EM>First Registration (June 15 to Dec 31): </EM></STRONG>		$25.<P>
	<STRONG><EM>Annual Supplemental Certificate of Authority:</EM></STRONG>	$25.<P>
	<STRONG><EM>First Registration (June 15 to Dec 31):</EM></STRONG>			$12.50.<P>
	<STRONG><EM>Additional Identification Cards:	</EM></STRONG>			$ 2.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
