<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Illinois Vehicle Emissions Program</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Vehicle Emissions Program
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Secretary of State<BR>
Driver Services Department<BR>
2701 South Dirksen Parkway<BR>
Springfield, IL 62723<BR>
(217) 785-9440<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.	Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
625 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/Section 13A-101.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 35, Illinois Administrative Code, Part 276.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Every motor vehicle owned by a resident of the "original inspection area", other than an exempt vehicle, is subject to inspection under this program.  The "original inspection area" means Cook county and portions of DuPage, Lake, Madison & St. Clair  counties. <P>

The purpose of the program is to reduce the emission of pollutants by motor vehicles.    <P>

Failure to subject a vehicle to an inspection order or failure to properly display the sticker is a petty offense.  Anyone guilty of three (3) offenses in a year is guilty of a Class C misdemeanor.  Fines may range from $50 - $300.<P>

The inspection stickers expires on the last day of the third month following the month assigned  either for initial inspection or the vehicle's next inspection.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Vehicle inspections may be performed only by inspectors who have successfully completed an approved training course and at official inspection stations with equipment that has been approved by the Agency.<P>

Inspections consist of an exhaust gas analysis and, if required, a tamper check.  Vehicles will be deemed to have passed such tests if the exhaust gas sample indicates that the concentrations of pollutants emitted by the vehicle do not exceed the standards set for vehicles of that type.  If all required tests are passed at the time of the inspection, the owner of the vehicle (or his/her agent) shall be entitled to an emission inspection sticker.<P>

The owner of a vehicle to be inspected may not be expected to wait more than 15 minutes from the time of presenting the vehicle for inspection and the actual start of the inspection.<P>

An owner or lessee of a fleet of 15 or more vehicles subject to inspection may apply to the Department for a permit to establish and operate a Private Official Inspection Station. <P>

Grievances must be filed on forms prescribed by the Agency within 15 days of occurrence of the incident.  The Agency then has a 30-day investigation period within which to make a decision and issue written notification.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. 	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
