<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Registration Statement for Credit Services Organization</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.  Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration Statement for Credit Services Organization
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Secretary of State<BR>
Index Department<BR>
111 East Monroe Street<BR>
Springfield, IL 62756<BR>
(217) 782-7017<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III.  Statute: </H3>
<DL><DD>
815 Illinois Compiled Statutes 605/9 (Credit Services Organization Act)
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
14 Illinois Administrative Code 177
</DD></DL>
 
<HR>
<H3>IV.  Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The purpose of this Act is to provide prospective consumers of credit services companies with the information necessary to make an informed decision regarding the purchase of those services and to protect the public from unfair or deceptive advertising and business practices.  Credit Service Organizations* (CSO) must file a Registration Statement with the Secretary of State, Index Department, before conducting business in Illinois.<P>

Violators of this Act are liable for damages, and may be convicted of a
Class A misdemeanor for a first offense, and Class 4 felony for subsequent
offenses.<P>

*A "CSO" is a business that provides any of the following services:  (1)
improving a buyer's credit record, history or rating, (2) obtaining an
extension of credit for a buyer or (3) providing advice or assistance to a
buyer with regard to either (1) or (2) above. (Exceptions to this
definition include businesses under governmental supervision such as banks,
savings and loans eligible for FDIC insurance, credit unions, some non-
profit organizations, real estate brokers, attorneys, broker-dealers
registered with the Securities Exchange Commission, and consumer reporting
agencies.)<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Registration Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A CSO may contact the Secretary of State Index Department to receive a "Credit Services Organization Registration Statement".  Prior to conducting business, the registration statement must be filed in the Index Department along with a $100 filing fee.  A surety bond of $100,000 may also be filed for organizations that "charge or receive any money or other valuable consideration prior to full and complete performance of any services the credit services organization has agreed to perform for or on behalf of the buyer."  The Index Department will process the registration statement in approximately one week.   A CSO must update their registration within 90 days of any change in information listed on the original statement.  The registration remains in effect until the organization ceases to do business in Illinois.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.  Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Registration fee: $100
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
