<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: School Bus Driver Permit</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement  Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
School Bus Driver Permit
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Secretary of State<BR>
Driver Services Department<BR>
2701 South Dirksen Parkway<BR>
Springfield, IL 62723<BR>
(217) 782-7674<BR>
</DD></DL>

<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
625 Illinois Compiled Statutes Act 5/Section 6-106.1.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 92, Illinois Administrative Code, Part 448.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. 	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Permit is required to drive a school bus.<P>

The purpose for requiring a permit is to assist in obtaining well-qualified individuals to serve as school bus drivers throughout the state.  <P>

Driving a school bus without a proper Permit is a petty offense
for the first violation and a Class B misdemeanor for
subsequent violations.<P>

Permits are valid for one year and may be renewed. To re-apply, a renewal application must be filed with certification verifying the completion of a yearly physical and refresher training.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V. 	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must complete a pre-employment interview with the prospective employer to determine acceptability, then obtain forms from the prospective employer and complete the following:  Application for Illinois School Bus Driver permit; Medical Examiner's Certificate; and fingerprint process including background investigations by Illinois State Police and FBI.  Employers must certify that applicant has satisfied all requisite conditions of employment.  Applicants may then file the employer's certification, a school bus driver application and appropriate fee.  Upon review of the applicant's driving history, the applicant must pass a written examination and must complete a road test for the class of vehicle to be used.  <P>

Tests must be successfully completed in three attempts and within 90 days from the date of certification by the employer.<P>

If an applicant successfully completes all pre-employment conditions and examination requirements, the Secretary of State will issue a school bus driver permit with a provisional status, which will be removed upon successfully passing the FBI criminal background investigation.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
None.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees: </H3>
<DL><DD>
<STRONG><EM>1.) Original School Bus Driver Permit & Renewal of School Bus Driver Permit:</EM></STRONG> $4<P>

<STRONG><EM>2.) Duplicate or Corrected Permit:</EM> </STRONG>$4<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
