<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Uniform Commercial Code Act </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Uniform Commercial Code Act 
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Secretary of State<BR>
Dept. of Business Services/Uniform Commercial Code Division<BR>
Room 30 Howlett Office Building<BR>
Springfield, IL 62756<BR>
(217) 782-7518<BR>
TDD: (800) 252-2904 or (217) 524-1137 (hearing impaired use only)	<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
810 Illinois Compiled Statutes 5/9-4
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
14 Illinois Administrative Code, Subtitle A, 1/180
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
The primary purpose of this Act is to provide and maintain accurate records of secured transactions, amendments, partial releases, continuations, assignments, terminations and tax liens and to make those records available to the public upon written request. The Act provides a means to perfect a security interest in non-titled collateral. Financing statements are how a lender perfects a lien to secure collateral used in financial transactions. Statements remain in effect for 5 years.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A financing statement is secured by submitting Form# UCC-1, signed by all Debtor(s) to the Secretary of State. Any subsequent filings are submitted on Form# UCC-3 form referencing the original filing to execute either: a continuation (renewal prior to the 5 year expiration); partial release (releases a part of the secured collateral); assignment (assigns secured rights to a third party); amendment (any change other than those stated above); or termination (filed by secured party of record at time of payment in full). <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Pre-Requisite:</EM> Form# UCC-3 must be signed in ink by the Secured Party of Record.<P>

<EM>Co-Requisite:</EM> Continuations must be filed within a 6 month period prior to the 5 year expiration of the financing statement in order to maintain a security interest in any collateral from date of original filing. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Filing a Financing or Subsequent Statements on prescribed form:  $4 per debtor name/address.<P>

Attachments or use of non-standard forms is an additional $4.<P>

Search fees are $10 per debtor name plus $1.00 for each page that is requested to be copied.  Walk-in customers may "view" documents without charge.<P>

The cost to file a Federal Tax Lien is $5 for the first debtor and $1 for each additional debtor. Copies of Federal Tax Liens are $.50 per page.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
