<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Formation of a Limited Partnership</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Formation of a Limited Partnership
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Secretary of State<BR>
Dept. of Business Services / Limited Partnership Division<BR>
Room 357 Howlett Office Building<BR>
Springfield, IL 62756<BR>
(217) 785-8960<BR>
TDD:  (800) 252-2904 or (217) 524-1137 (hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
805 Illinois Compiled Statutes 210
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
14 Illinois Administrative Code, Subtitle A, I / 170
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A limited partnership is formed by 2 or more persons and contains 1 or more general partners and 1 or more limited partners. A limited partnership differs from a general partnership in that it provides a passive investor a way to contribute capital to the partnership without incurring liability beyond his original investment.  The true name of the partnership must include the words "limited partnership" or the abbreviation "L.P.". An application may be filed to adopt an assumed name and it must comply with the same requirements of a true name. Renewal reports must be filed every two years prior to the partnership's anniversary date on a form provided by the Secretary of State. Limited partnerships are perpetually effective.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit a "Certificate of Limited Partnership" to the Secretary of State. The certificate is not effective until the filing date or by a delayed date specified within the certificate. The certificate must be signed only by all general partners. Applications may be denied for non-compliance with the Act. Denied applications may be corrected and resubmitted.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Pre-Requisite: </EM>Applicants must appoint and maintain a registered agent and a registered office in the State of Illinois.<P>

<EM>Co-Requisite:</EM>  Applicants must provide a Federal Identification Number (FEIN) to the Secretary of State within 180 days of filing a Certificate of Limited Partnership.  Failure to comply puts the partnership delinquent on the Secretary of State's records. <P>

<EM>Post-Requisite: </EM>	A certificate of cancellation must be filed by the partnership when it is dissolved and has ceased to do business.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
		Certificate of Limited Partnership		$ 75<BR>
		Amendments						$ 25<BR>
		Renewal assumed name				$150<BR>
		Reinstatement						$100<BR>
		Penalty							$100<BR>
		Cancellation						$ 25<BR>
		Renewal Report						$ 15<BR>
		File copies and abstracts			$ 10<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
