<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Formation of a Limited Liability Company (LLC)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.	Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Formation of a Limited Liability Company (LLC)
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.	Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Secretary of State<BR>
Department of Business Services / (LLC) Division<BR>
Room 359 Howlett Office Building<BR>
Springfield, IL 62756<BR>
(217) 524-8008<BR>
TDD:	(800) 252-2904 or (217) 524-1137 (hearing impaired use only)<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
805 Illinois Compiled Statutes 180
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
14 Illinois Administrative Code, Subtitle A, I / 178
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV.	Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Limited Liability Company's (LLCs) differ from partnerships and corporations in that they combine the advantage of limited liability with pass through tax advantage. LLCs allow for flexibility by providing for management either by the members or managers, or a combination of both. The true name of LLCs is subject to name availability within the LLC records of current filings and must include the words "limited liability company" or the abbreviation "L.L.C.". Applications may be filed to adopt an assumed name but it must comply with the same requirements of a true name. An LLC may be administratively dissolved for non-compliance of the Act. Registration of LLCs remains on record for one year. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.	Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must submit the "Articles of Organization" for filing with the Secretary of State. The Articles are not effective until the filing date or by a delayed date specified within the articles not to exceed 60 days. An LLC must have 2 or more owners called members. An organizer need not be a member of the LLC. Articles of Organization may be denied if the information is incorrect, or for non-compliance with the Act. Articles which have been denied may be corrected and resubmitted.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI.	Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites:</H3>
<DL><DD>
<EM>Pre-Requisite:</EM> Applicants must provide a Federal Employee Identification Number (FEIN) to the Secretary of State within 90 days of filing the Articles. Applicants must appoint and maintain a registered agent and a registered office in the State of Illinois. <P>

<EM>Co-Requisite:</EM> Amendments may be filed at any time for additions, deletions or changes to any existing provision of the Articles. The effective date of an amendment is the filing date or within a specified period of time not to exceed 30 days following the filing date. To remain in good standing, LLCs must submit an annual report. These reports must be filed prior to the first day of their anniversary month on a form provided by the Secretary of State.<P>

<EM>Post-Requisite:</EM> Articles of dissolution must be filed with the Secretary of State by the LLC when all debts, liabilities and obligations have been discharged and all assets have been distributed. <P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII.	Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
	Articles of Organization		$500<BR>
	Amendments				$100<BR>
	Renewal assumed name		$300<BR>
	Reinstatement				$500<BR>
	Reserved name				$300<BR>
	Articles of Dissolution		$100<BR>
	Annual Report				$300<BR>
	File copies and abstracts	$ 25<BR>
</DD></DL>


<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
