<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>First Stop: Permit to Move Oversize/Overweight Objects on State Highways</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#004080" LINK="#004080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/fs/fslogosm.gif" alt="First Stop Logo" width=171 height=120 align=left>
<h3 align=center>Department of Commerce & Community Affairs
<hr>
First Stop Business Information Center<br>
Business Requirement
</h3>
<hr>
<br clear=all>

<H3>I.   Business Requirement Profile:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Permit to Move Oversize/Overweight Objects on State Highways
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>II.  Agency:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Illinois Department of Transportation<BR>
Division of Highways<BR>
2300 South Dirksen Parkway<BR>
Springfield, IL 62764<BR>
(217) 785-8967<BR>
Fax # (217) 782-3572<BR>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>III. Statute:</H3>
<DL><DD>
625 Illinois Compiled Statutes, Act 5/Section 15-301.
</DD></DL>
<H3>Regulation:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Title 92, Illinois Administrative Code, Part 554.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>IV. Requirement Description:</H3>
<DL><DD>
A Permit is required before any oversize or overweight object may be moved on the State highway system. This requirement most often applies to trucking firms that haul oversize/overweight objects.<P>

Operating without a Permit is a petty offense. First offender fines range from $50 to $200, second offense fines range from $200-$300 and third offense fines range from $300-$500.<P>

A Permit is effective until the move for which the Permit was issued has been completed.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>V.  Approval Process:</H3>
<DL><DD>
Applicants must first arrange a method of payment by (1) establishing an account with the Department, (2) calling a Permit Service to apply for the applicant, or (3) arranging for the Permit to be sent C.O.D. to a truck stop.<P>

A Routine Permit for a load limit of 120,000 pounds gross weight, a height of 15 feet, a width of 14.5 feet, and/or 145 feet long can be obtained by calling (217) 785-8967 outside of Illinois and 1-800-252-8636 within Illinois.  Form #BT-1928 is used for Routine Permits.  A special form is used for weights and dimensions in excess of those listed above and completed applications must be faxed to the Department for review.<P>    

Application review is usually completed in 2-4 hours.  Under certain circumstances, applications for exceptionally wide or high moves can take as many as 7 working days for authorization.<P>

Applications may be denied for objects that are too large or heavy for the highway system; objects that do not meet the legal definition of a permitable item or if applicants are not able to pay for a Permit.<P>
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VI. Pre-Requisites, Co-Requisites & Post-Requisites: </H3>
<DL><DD>
Owners and/or operators of vehicles with loads wider than 10 feet must have insurance in effect, or be self-insured, in the minimum amount of $500,000 per occurrence (combined injury and property damage).<P>

If hauling for-hire, applicant must have a Certificate of Authority from the Illinois Commerce Commission.<P>	
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<H3>VII. Fees:</H3>
<DL><DD>
There are overdimension, overweight, and overweight-axle fees.  Fees vary widely for each category and applicants may contact the Department for exact information on fees.
</DD></DL>

<HR>
<STRONG>| <a href="/dcca/home.htm">DCCA Home Page</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsm1.htm">First Stop</a> | <A HREF="/dcca/menus/fsbr.htm">Business Requirements</a> |</STRONG>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
