<h3 align=center>
November 15, 1996<p>
DCCA to Host Competitive Communities Workshops
</h3>

<strong>SPRINGFIELD, ILL. </strong> --  Illinois communities interested in participating in the Competitive Communities Initiative (CCI) administered by the Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs (DCCA) are encouraged to attend one of three workshops to be held next week.<p>

Lt. Gov. Bob Kustra, Governor Edgar's senior advisor for economic development, said the program is designed to give local governments the tools to help themselves become more competitive. <p>

"The Competitive Communities Initiative is one of  DCCA's most popular local government programs," said Kustra.  "Economic development opportunities often hinge on how prepared a community is for growth.  A community of any size or level of economic development sophistication that is determined to improve itself can benefit from the rigorous self-assessment and action plan developed as the result of this program."  <p>

DCCA Director Dennis Whetstone said the program is already successfully in place in 30 communities throughout Illinois.<p>  

"CCI helps communities focus on leadership, assess their foundations for growth and build upon past economic development efforts," said Whetstone.  "Mayors and other local leaders have told us that their participation in CCI has helped them identify local development issues and develop consensus."<p>

Application workshops will be held in three different locations during the week of November 18, 1996.  At the workshops, CCI staff members will give a brief description of the goals and objectives of CCI and answer any questions concerning the application process.  Communities do not have to attend a workshop in order to submit an application.<p>

Applications are due no later than December 16, 1996 at the Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs, Office of Local Initiatives, 620 E. Adams Street, Springfield, Illinois  62701.<p>

The workshops will be held at the following locations:<p>

November 18, 1996<br>
Mt. Vernon City Building West<br>
200 Potomac Boulevard<br>
Mt. Vernon, Illinois 62864<br>
6:30 pm - 8:30 pm.<p>
  
November 20, 1996<br>
Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs<br>
(Theater)  <br>
620 E. Adams<br>
Springfield, Illinois 62701<br>
2:00 pm - 4:00 pm<p>

November 21, 1996<br>
Beecher Community Building	<br>
908 Game Farm Road<br>
Yorkville, Illinois 60560<br>
6:30 pm - 8:30 pm <p>

Questions about the workshops or the application process may be directed to Jeff Markland of the Office of Local Initiatives, 217/524-1931 (TDD 800/785-6055).<br>




