<h3 align=center>
September 5, 1996<p>
Edgar Statement about State & Federal Grants for the Illinois Manufacturing Extension Centers
</h3>

Gov. Jim Edgar issued the following statement about the state and federal grants announced today for the Illinois Manufacturing Extension Center:<p>

"We're delighted that federal officials agree with us that Illinois small and medium-sized manufacturers need and deserve public support as they strive to take full advantage of global market opportunities and grow stronger.<p>

"Only a diverse and supportive economic climate for small businesses can create the good-paying manufacturing jobs Illinoisans need and want.<p>

"This first-year federal grant for the Illinois Manufacturing Extension Center, coupled with the Edgar administration's financial support over the past few years, means our state's small- and medium-sized businesses can enjoy an even more comprehensive level of technical support and assistance as they seek to enhance productivity, improve technology and compete more effectively.<p>

"The establishment of the center as an independent, not-for-profit corporation, and its planned expansion to better serve companies across the state shows the positive impact of public/private partnerships as we in Illinois continue to lead in our efforts to foster innovative, cost-effective ways to help Illinois businesses improve."<p>

<center><strong>###</strong></center>
	 
