<HEAD><TITLE>DCCA: 1995 Annual Report -- Bureau of Energy & Recycling</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000080" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#0080C0" ALINK="#0080C0">

<img src="/dcca/graph/logosm.jpg" alt="DCCA Logo" width=165 height=82 align=left>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<h3>
Department of Commerce & Community Affairs<p>
</h3>
<img src="/dcca/graph/cbar.gif" width=410 height=4><p>
<FONT SIZE=+3>1995 Annual Report: Bureau of Energy & Recycling *</FONT>
<BR CLEAR=RIGHT>
<HR>
<p>

The Bureau of Energy and Recycling promotes the efficient and economic use of Illinois' energy resources and offers both financial and technical assistance to promote alternative methods to manage waste.  The Department is the lead agency under the Solid Waste Management Act, and is directed to encourage and promote such alternative waste management efforts as source reduction, reuse and recycling.<p>


<h4>
<a href="#Office of Recycling">Office of Recycling & Waste Reduction</a><p>
<ul type=square>
<li><a href="#Materials Recycling">Materials Recycling Unit</a><br>
<li><a href="#Market Development">Market Development</a><br>
<li><a href="#ICAP">Illinois College Assistance Program (ICAP)</a><br>
<li><a href="#Used Tire Recovery">Used Tire Recovery</a><br>
<li><a href="#Solid Waste Management">Solid Waste Management Research</a><br>
<li><a href="#Tech Demonstration">Technology Demonstration</a><br>
<li><a href="#School Education">School Education Program</a><p>
</ul>


<a href="#Energy Conservation & Alternative Energy">Office of Energy Conservation & Alternative Energy</a><p>
<ul type=square>
<li><a href="#Affordable Housing">Affordable Housing Program</a><br>
<li><a href="#Ethanol Programs">Ethanol Programs</a><br>
<li><a href="#Assist to Agriculture">Assistance to Agriculture</a><br>
<li><a href="#Energy Wise Homes">Energy Wise Homes of Illinois</a><br>
<li><a href="#Energy Performance">Energy Performance Contracting</a><br>
<li><a href="#Energy Efficiency">Energy Efficiency in State Buildings</a><br>
<li><a href="#ICP">Institutional Conservation Program (ICP)</a><br>
<li><a href="#Telecommuting">Telecommuting & Transportation Programs</a><br>
<li><a href="#Energy Emergency Preparedness">Energy Emergency Preparedness</a><br>
