<CENTER><H3>Coal Demonstration Program</H3></CENTER>
<HR>
<H4>
The Illinois Coal Demonstration Program supports development of state-
of-the-art development/demonstration projects for advanced coal
systems for utility and industrial use.  Funding is provided through
the Illinois Coal and Energy Development Bond Fund, with co-funding
from the public and private sectors.  The projects help bring a new
generation of clean coal techniques to the commercial marketplace and
provide near-term benefits to the state and local communities through
increased employment, personal income and tax revenues.<P>

For information call 217/785-2780.<P>
