<CENTER><H3>Illinois Coal Development Board</H3></CENTER>
<HR>
<H4>
Comprised of 13 public and statutory members appointed by the
Governor, the Illinois Coal Development Board reviews and approves all
coal research, development and demonstration projects, and also
approves expenditures from the Coal Technology Development Assistance
Fund and the Coal and Energy Development Bond Fund.  The ICCI Program
Committee, the Clean Coal Research Association and the Coal Energy
Advisory Committee assist the Board in setting the state's coal
research agenda.  The Board provides annual updates to the Governor
and General Assembly in the state-mandated report, Outlook for the
Illinois Coal Industry.<P>

For information call 217/785-6370.<P>
