<CENTER><H3>Solid Waste Management Research Program</H3></CENTER>
<HR>

<h3>Purpose</h3>

The research program supports applied and basic research on solid waste management problems.  The program will also help businesses and communities connect with University researchers when such resources are required to solve specific problems with recovering or reusing recycled materials or reducing solid waste generation.<p>

<h3>Eligibility</h3>

Public or private research colleges and universities in Illinois may apply for funding.<p>

<h3>Funding</h3>

Funding is provided through two competitive grant rounds annually.  Grants up to $100,000 are available.  No applicant investments are required by partnering with Illinois businesses and communities is strongly encouraged.  Projects with applicant investment s will be given higher priority.  Funding for indirect costs, P.I. salaries, and equipment purchases are limited.  All projects must include graduate student participation.<p>

<h3>Further Information</h3>

For further information, contact: Dr. Roger Minear, Office of Solid Waste Research, Institute for Environmental Studies, University of Illinois at Urbana/Champaign, 217/333-2503 or Ron Swager, Manager, Education, Research & Development Section, Bureau of Energy & Recycling, Illinois Department of Commerce and Community Affairs at 217/785-3498.  TDD customers may call 217/785-0211.<p>

